Name: Piccolomon
Summary: A Fairy Digimon that is fluent in magic. It can recite the advanced programming language of another dimension, allowing it to generate miracles with the appearance of magic. This miraculous Digimon is able to pop up in every place, time, and space, and although its body is small, it can seal away the enemy's abilities with its own special ability, and then pulverize the opponent with a mighty blow. With its mischief-loving personality, it enjoys making computers run wild with its cherished spear, "Fairy Tale", that it always holds in its hands (although it has no ill intent).

Name: Pumpkinmon
Summary: Pumpkinmon is a plush toy Digimon with a pumpkin head. There's an urban legend that says Pumpmon came to be when mutations developed in a computer virus created during the season of the Western holiday of "Halloween". However, though it doesn't inflict any harm at all because it was not a malignant virus, its external appearance belies its possession of powerful offensive ability. As you can tell even from looking at its blank face, a rare expression of emotions is characteristic of Puppet Digimon.

Name: Ranamon
Summary: Ranamon serves as a villain from Digimon Frontier. Cherubimon created her from the spirits of water of AncientMermaimon making her the Legendary Warrior of Water.

Name: Ronan the Accuser (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ronan the Accuser is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is a judicial officer of the fictional alien race known as the Kree. Although usually portrayed as a supervillain, he is sometimes depicted as a more noble and honorable character.

Name: Sakuyamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Sandiramon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Snake. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Zhuqiaomon, it is the most cunning and cruel among the Deva. It doesn't like to decide matches in an instant, and prefers to instead choke the life out of the opponent while tormenting them bit by bit. It usually lives deep beneath the ground, and subterranean maneuvers are its specialty. During battle, it can produce a spear made of light, the Bǎo Kuí, from its mouth, and skillfully wield it with its tail wrapped around it like a hand. Although the Bǎo Kuí vanishes once it slashes the opponent, as long as Sandiramon's energy lasts, it can spit out any number of them, and they will not degrade in sharpness.

Name: Scorpiomon
Summary: A computer virus infected the databanks of a laboratory where the investigations and excavations of ancient life forms is performed, and took in the data of an ancient life form and evolved. It became like the life form which in ancient times was the apex of the food chain, which had a great appetite and supplied it with an ability capable of allowing it to see food that was of the finest quality. Skillfully using the tentacles that grow from its head, it catches the enemy and kills them with the sharp blade that grows from its tail. When the progression of a fight becomes disadvantageous, it uses its sharp tentacles to hoist up the soil of the seabed to hide its body. The radar eye that projects from its head captures the enemy like a night vision scope, watching for the chance to create a turnabout.

Name: ShogunGekomon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Sinduramon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Rooster. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Baihumon, it likes to quarrel and gossip above all else. With its provocative attitude, it will pick a fight with its opponent one way or another, but when they move to attack, it immediately draws its head and wings within its spherical armor. Its armor is the hardest among all of the Deva's equipment, and once it gets inside of the armor, it is absolutely protected. During battle, it is occasionally possible to cut through the breach when it rolls around in that state.

Name: Sirenmon
Summary: Sirenmon is a God Man Digimon which has an outward appearance like a blending of bird and fish. Its personality is cheerful, and it is always singing pleasant songs throughout the skies and seas. Its voice has a miraculously sweet sound and actually has an eight octave range from very high notes to very low notes, and it brings tranquility even to devastated battlefields with its singing voice.

Name: Sora (Ninjago)
Summary: Sora (originally born as Ana) is the Elemental Master of Technology and a smart inventor. Born in Imperium, she was one of the smartest inventor of her Realm, but after seeing how her kingdom mistreated the dragons and being disowned by her parents, she left her home following the Merge and befriended Arin, changing her name to "Sora". She later on meet Lloyd and became one of his ninja students, eventually reaching her True Potential in a fight against the evil Empress Beatrix

Name: Sphinx (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Anath-Na Mut better known as Sphinx is a recurring villain of Nova who first appeared in Nova Vol 1 6. From there on he'd proceed to also fight the likes of the Fantastic Four and the New Warriors. Anath-Na Mut was the chief wizard for Pharaoh during his reign, but after he lost the battle to Moses,[1] he was exiled from the empire. Walking the sands of Egypt for 90 years, Anath-Na Mut found the Ka Stone. Upon placing the stone on his forehead, Anath-Na Mut was forever transformed into a deathless immortal who is doomed to walk this earth forever.[2]

Name: Starmon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Thanos (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thanos, referred to as the Dark Lord by his most loyal underlings and the Mad Titan by the galactic community, is a powerful Titan warlord who rules over a distant region of space and commands two massive armies, known as the Chitauri and the Outriders, and a small group of followers known as the Black Order whom he adopted as his children. His main objective was to bring stability from the universe, as he believed its massive population would inevitably use up the universe's resources and condemn it. However, his methodology to succeed was warped; through the use of the ancient Infinity Stones, he intended to harness their power to exterminate half of all life in the universe, thus returning it to what he perceived to be a state of cosmic balance.

Name: Tyrannomon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least 6-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | 1-C

Name: Universal Weapon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Universal Weapon, also known as Cosmi-Rod, is one of the main weapons of the Kree race, being used by powerful Kree who managed to reach the highest rank in the Kree army, Supreme Accuser. It's most commonly known wielder is Ronan the Accuser, who made multiple appearances on Earth to enforce the Kree laws using the powers of of the weapon. It's currently being wielded by Lauri-Ell that is protecting the current emperor of the Kree/Skrull alliance Dorrek-Vell.

Name: WarGreymon
Summary: An ultimate form of Greymon-species Digimon, it is a subspecies of War Greymon armed with electric-powered weapons.

Name: Wonder Woman (Golden Age)
Summary: Tier: 4-C

Name: Aatrox
Summary: Once honored defenders of Shurima against the Void, Aatrox and his brethren would eventually become an even greater threat to Runeterra, and were defeated only by cunning mortal sorcery. But after centuries of imprisonment, Aatrox was the first to find freedom once more, corrupting and transforming those foolish enough to try and wield the magical weapon that contained his essence. Now, with stolen flesh, he walks Runeterra in a brutal approximation of his previous form, seeking an apocalyptic and long overdue vengeance.

Name: AeroVeedramon
Summary: A small, blue-colored, Dragon Digimon child. Although it is small and powerless, it has the potential to evolve to every Dragon Digimon. For that reason, it is a Digimon that is considered exceedingly valuable by tamers and researchers of Dragon Digimon. It is cherished due to its personality of friendliness and overflowing curiosity, characteristic of Baby Digimon. Just like other Baby Digimon, it spits acidic bubbles to attack, but as usual, their power is nonexistent.

Name: Aether (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Reality Stone is one of the six Infinity Stones, the remnant of a singularity that predated the universe, which represents the fabric of reality. Liquefied into a dark red fluid called the Aether (pronounced ēTHər), the Dark Elves and their leader Malekith intended to use it to revert the universe to its state of primordial darkness. The Aether was taken from the Elves by the Asgardians and entrusted to the Collector following the Second Dark Elf Conflict.

Name: Ahri
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 7-A | 4-B | 4-B

Name: Algomon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C, up to 1-C

Name: Anivia
Summary: Anivia is a benevolent winged spirit who endures endless cycles of life, death, and rebirth to protect the Freljord. A demigod born of unforgiving ice and bitter winds, she wields those elemental powers to thwart any who dare disturb her homeland. Anivia guides and protects the tribes of the harsh north, who revere her as a symbol of hope, and a portent of great change. She fights with every ounce of her being, knowing that through her sacrifice, her memory will endure, and she will be reborn into a new tomorrow.

Name: Annihilus
Summary: Annihilus, a native of the planet Arthos, is the ruler of The Negative Zone and a longtime foe of The Fantastic Four.

Name: Antylamon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Rabbit. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Qinglongmon, it is the owner of a gentle spirit. It likes small things, and because it attends to them with profound tenderness, if anything appears that tries to tread on them then its personality is completely reversed, and it attacks with the Bǎo Fǔ which transformed its hands into razor-sharp axes. Once a cut is made, it won't stop spreading until the enemy's form is no more.

Name: Aquaman (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Arthur Curry is Aquaman, an adventurer who is half-human and half-Atlantean. This gives him a variety of powers including superhuman strength, telepathic control over marine life, and the ability to survive both in water and on land. He belongs to the royal family of Atlantis, and normally acts as their king. His romantic partner is the princess Mera of Xebel. He is a founding member of two superhero teams, the world-famous Justice League and the clandestine Others

Name: Arbormon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Archnemon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Arin (Ninjago)
Summary: Arin is a self-taught Spinjitzu prodigy, creator of Object Spinjitzu, and one of Lloyd's ninja students. He is the first known person to teach himself Spinjitzu without a master. He used to live in a neighbourhood outside Ninjago City, until the Merge caused his parents and region to dissappear. Multiple years after the Merge, Arin and his best friend Sora became students of the Green Ninja Lloyd Garmadon after saving a dragon called Riyu. With the help of the other original ninja, Arin helped to free most of the dragons from Imperium. He and Lloyd searched for the Pink Dragon Core, defeat Beatrix, and helped to stabilize the Merged Realms during the MergeQuake Storm, where he saw his parents through a rift.

Name: Aspheera
Summary: Aspheera is the former leader of the Pyro Vipers and an Hypnobrai sorceress who seeks revenge against Wu, who betrayed her thousands of years ago. After getting released from her tomb, she stole Kai's powers and began a rampage on Ninjago City in order to find the scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu and confront Wu, only to banish Zane instead in the Never Realm. Sometimes after getting locked in the Kryptarium Prison, she was freed from her cell by the Ninjas in order to turn Nya back to her human form. Later on, she joined the Overlord's army only to be defeated by Kai and Zane in the final battle to save the Realm of Ninjago from being plunged into darkness.

Name: Atsuko Kagari
Summary: Despite being born to a fully human non-magic family, Atsuko "Akko" Kagari harbored a dream of becoming like her idol "Shiny" Chariot du Nord after visiting one of her magic shows. To accomplish this dream, she enrolled in Luna Nova Academy after hearing it was accepting non-magical students due to it being the school where Shiny Chariot graduated. Though she struggles with magic due to her non-magical lineage, her determination allows her to overcome whatever problem faces her down.

Name: Aurico
Summary: Aurico is the Red Aquitar Ranger who is second-in-command of the Aquitar Rangers. He is also referred to as Red Alien Ranger by people of Earth, as well as Mighty Morphin Alien Red Ranger, a variation on his alternate in-show label, though it is more in reference to the show itself than a proper label.

Name: Azir
Summary: Azir was a mortal emperor of Shurima in a far distant age, a proud man who stood at the cusp of immortality. His hubris saw him betrayed and murdered at the moment of his greatest triumph, but now, millennia later, he has been reborn as an Ascended being of immense power. With his buried city risen from the sand, Azir seeks to restore Shurima to its former glory.

Name: B-0 (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Subject B-0, also known as Bizarro, was an imperfect clone of Superman who was taken out of his cloning tube early to help save the world from the reign of the Crime Syndicate. Although he did Luthor's bidding, he was a gentle and kind soul who only wanted to make those around him happy.

Name: BanchoLilimon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, possibly higher

Name: Bass.EXE
Summary: Bass.EXE is the world's first Independent NetNavi and an incredibly powerful rival of MegaMan.EXE. Cold, callous, and calculating, he only seeks to become as strong as he can be and will crush any who stands in his way. Designed by Dr. Cossack, he was created to test the limits of security systems and diffuse situations that would be too dangerous for any Operator to enter. Unfortunately, he was designed too well, and Cossack's superiors became terrified of Bass's growing power and feared that the Navi would one day take over the net, leading to his imprisonment.

Name: Batman (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Batman is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics. The character was created by artist Bob Kane and writer Bill Fsuinger, and first appeared in Detective Comics #27 (May 1939). Originally named "the Bat-Man", the character is also referred to by such epithets as the "Caped Crusader," the "Dark Knight," and the "World's Greatest Detective".

Name: Black Hole Collision Event
Summary: A Black Hole Collision event is the occurrence in which two black holes spiral around each other and eventually merge, resulting in energy roughly equivalent to the mass of the sun being converted into gravitational waves that will ripple through the fabric of space-time.

Name: Black Orchid (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Black Orchid, real name Alba Garcia, is a superhuman who gained her abilities from a series of mysterious experiments which gave her ties to both The Red and The Green, elemental forces which respectively pervade all animal and plant life. Her ties with A.R.G.U.S. led her to become an agent of the Justice League Dark for a while, but she has since quit and disappeared to learn more about her past

Name: BlackWarGreymon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C, Likely 1-C

Name: Blitzcrank
Summary: Tier: 7-B | 7-B | 4-B

Name: Brainiac (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Vril Dox was once a higly intelligent but neglectful scientist who doomed his entire race, including his family to further his own goals. As the supervillain Brainiac, he has been a consistant threat to not only Superman, but the entire human race on numerous occansions. Though primary a solo-threat, Brainiac has teamed up with other villains, such as Lex Luthor, Doomsday, Metallo, and Cyborg Superman, the latter three by force.

Name: Brainiac (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Brainiac was a robot from the distant future who traveled the universe, shrinking cities for his own self-satisfaction. He was among Superman's greatest and most fearsome foes. Though he lacked in physical strength, he more than made up for it with his unmatched mind, arsenal of futuristic weapons and shockingly good agility. After what could have been his final outing involving a weapon known as the Planet-Eater, Brainiac's body was transformed into the New Brainiac, a bio-robot who absorbed all the knowedge in the universe, and embarked on a new quest, a quest that would never be fufilled, to overthrow God himself.

Name: Brand
Summary: Once a tribesman of the icy Freljord named Kegan Rodhe, the creature known as Brand is a lesson in the temptation of greater power. Seeking one of the legendary World Runes, Kegan betrayed his companions and seized it for himself—and, in an instant, the man was no more. His soul burned away, his body a vessel of living flame, Brand now roams Valoran in search of other Runes, swearing revenge for wrongs he could never possibly have suffered in a dozen mortal lifetimes.

Name: Brutaal (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: At some point in time, Darkseid managed to manufacture a clone of Kal-El in almost every facet. This clone had all of Kal's memories, including his upbringing with the Kents. However, it does not appear to have any memory of Val-Zod. This clone later on took the name of Brutaal

Name: Bryweludramon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | Low 1-C

Name: Cain (New 52)
Summary: Cain, the Sire of all Vampires, is a being far older than humanity, being born with the curse that he would spread across Earth, turning all of his victims into more faithful servants that he would eventually try to use to take over the world.

Name: Caitlyn (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 7-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, High 6-C with Weapons | At least 10-B, 4-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, At least 7-B with Weapons, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: Captain Atom (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Nathaniel Adam was an airforce captain before he became part of Doctor Heinrich Megala's experiment to prove the M-Theory correct and discover something amazing. However, the experiment was a failure and Nathaniel Adam was considered dead for a brief period of time. In reality, Nathaniel had become a phantom, a ghost who recreated a body for himself from nothing. Once he returned back from the "dead", Nathaniel found himself changed on the deepest level possible. With the new found power, Nathaniel became the Quantum-powered hero known as Captain Atom.

Name: Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell)
Summary: Captain Mar-Vell was a member of the Kree, the alien humanoid warrior race which has forged an empire throughout the galaxy known as the Large Magellanic Cloud. More specifically, he was one of the so-called "Pink Kree." This Kree race has the same color skin as Caucasian Earth humans, to whom those Kree who belong to it are more biologically similar than blue Kree are. As such he was chosen to act as a spy in his mission to conquer Earth, taking on the identity of the deceased Dr. Walter Lawson, however Earth and its denizens changed his views as he left the Kree Empire to be one of the Earth's greatest defenders, the original Captain Marvel

Name: Captain Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Captain Carol Susan Jane Danvers, also known as Captain Marvel, is a former United States Air Force pilot who, upon being exposed to the energy of the Tesseract, obtained cosmic powers. She was made into a Kree-Human hybrid via a blood transfusion from Yon-Rogg, while having her memories removed, turning her into the Kree's weapon and a member of Starforce. During the Kree's war with the Skrulls, Danvers returned to Earth and began recalling her past, with help from Nick Fury and Maria Rambeau. Danvers also discovered that Yon-Rogg had been manipulating her for years, learning from Talos that the Skrulls were merely seeking to find a new home. With this information, Danvers unlocked her true powers and defeated the Kree invasion onto Earth that was being led by Ronan the Accuser, before setting off out to the far reaches of the galaxy to finish what her late mentor Mar-Vell had once started.

Name: Caturamon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Dog. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Baihumon, it looks after its fellow followers Makuramon and Sinduramon as if they were its younger brothers (as for those two, it appears they do not feel the same degree of obligation). Its sense of justice is strong, and it is unsatisfied when it can't make something clear in black-and-white. When all of its comrades are quarreling, it will sometimes serve as a moderator or presiding judge, changing into the Bǎo Chuí, which is itself as a gigantic hammer, and passing judgment over guilt and innocence.

Name: Cerberumon
Summary: Cerberumon is a Demon Beast Digimon called the "Watchdog of Hell". The claws on its feet are hard enough to easily tear through Chrome Digizoid alloys, if they have a low purity. Also, its body is protected by a hard living shell, which has the ability to instantly repair any damage it incurs. The armor on its shoulders each possess sentience, and are able to instantly sense an attack coming from any direction, then report it to Cerberumon's central body.

Name: Cestro
Summary: Cestro is the Blue Aquitar Ranger of the Aquitar Rangers. He is also referred to as Blue Alien Ranger on Earth, as well as Mighty Morphin Alien Blue Ranger, a variation on his alternate in-show label, though it is more in reference to the show itself than a proper label.

Name: Cheetah (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: nan

Name: Cherrymon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Clouse
Summary: Clouse is Master Chen's former second-in-command and a master of Dark Magic. Like his master, Clouse has a history with Garmadon, having trained with him in their youth under Chen. During that time, he lost an opportunity to become Chen's right-hand man in a fight with Garmadon in the training yard, thus sparking his burning hatred against him.

Name: Constellate (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Constellates are large sentient star constellations that roam the night sky. Generally peaceful and avoiding conflict, they will fight with overwhelming force if necessary. They're connected by unknown means to the Aperusa

Name: Corki
Summary: The yordle pilot Corki loves two things above all others: flying, and his glamorous mustache... though not necessarily in that order. After leaving Bandle City, he settled in Piltover and fell in love with the wondrous machines he found there. He dedicated himself to the development of flying contraptions, leading an aerial defense force of seasoned veterans known as the Screaming Yipsnakes. Calm under fire, Corki patrols the skies around his adopted home, and has never encountered a problem that a good missile barrage couldn’t solve.

Name: Cyborg Superman (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Zor-El is a Kryptonian scientist, the father of Supergirl and uncle of Superman. He survived the destruction of his home planet, but was turned into the Cyborg Superman in the process.

Name: Dar-Benn (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Supremor Dar-Benn was a revolutionary Kree warrior and an Accuser of the Kree Empire who fought to restore her homeland after a long civil war. Formerly a member of Starforce, she blamed Captain Marvel for inciting a long civil war on Hala, which led to the planet's desolation. After discovering a Quantum Band on MB-418, Dar-Benn tore apart Jump Points in space to extract natural resources from various planets to restore her homeworld. She was eventually killed as a result of using two Quantum Bands at the same time.

Name: Dark Matter (Pokémon)
Summary: Dark Matter was born of negative emotions, an entity that wants to return the world and all life to the Void through destruction. When it first appeared it fought in a war against Pokémon, and a sole human, failing in its goal but not being truly defeated. Mew, a leading figure in the battle against Dark Matter reincarnated itself in the distant future to prevent the destruction it seeks when it was inevitably brought back.

Name: Darkseid (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Darkseid is one of the most powerful New Gods and the tyrannical ruler of Apokolips, an archetypal world beyond the boundaries of time and space. His everlasting goal is the utter domination and enslavement of all life in creation, when all is ordered according to his will.

Name: Deathstroke (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Slade Joseph Wilson, aka Deathstroke, joined the military at age sixteen, was an exceptional soldier and earned his fair share of medals. He volunteered for "Project X", which granted him enhanced reflexes, strength, mental capacity and rapid healing. After going AWOL in Bosnia, and winning his signature sword, he took on its name and began running covert black bag missions. It wasn't until after the death of his son that he became the world's deadliest assassin.

Name: Delphine (Power Rangers)
Summary: Delphine is the White Aquitar Ranger, and the leader of the Aquitar Rangers. She is also referred to as White Alien Ranger by people of Earth, as well as Mighty Morphin Alien White Ranger, a variation on her alternate in-show label, though it is more in reference to the show itself than a proper label.

Name: Dendar
Summary: Dendar is a primordial serpent that according to legend, came into existence as soon as the first being slept and had a nightmare. She has, for the eternity of the multiverse, consumed all of the most foul and dreaded nightmares and visions dreamt by mortals and deities alike and if not for her, all nightmares would be remembered in crucial details. It is said that she will also be the harbinger to the end of the world and the gods.

Name: Despero (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Despero is a conqueror of worlds and plunderer of civilizations. Though he fought the Justice League as a whole, he had a particular hatred for Martian Manhunter for being a 'traitor against his race'. Despero would later become an enemy of Hawkman and Adam Strange as he targeted Rann and Thanagar in his many conquests.

Name: Diablomon

Summary: Eaters are a group of higher dimensional digital lifeforms that appear the Digimon Story Cyber Sleuth and Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth Hacker's Memory. The Eaters are beings under the control of Mother Eater and serve as the overall main antagonists of the two Cyber Sleuth game.

Name: Ebemon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Etrigan (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Etrigan was once a rhyming demon of low standing, belittled by Lucifer, the lord of Hell. Fed up with his treatment, he decided to start a revolt, managing to get many demons to serve him due to his sheer battle prowess, but he couldn't hope to stand up to Lucifer, and was cast down to Earth, where the wizard Merlin fused him with his own unruly apprentice, Jason of Norwich, which would later go on to be known as Jason Blood.

Name: Ex-Tyranomon
Summary: Ex-Tyranomon is a Puppet Digimon that sneaks around within a Tyrannomon-shaped plush toy. The reason why it is a Tyranomon plush toy is unclear, but it is likely that the mysterious Digimon that is stealing away inside just broke into the plush toy that was closest. However, this plush toy possesses power rivaling that of Monzaemon at its limits and the defensive power of an impregnable fortress, so ordinary Digimon and the like are completely unable to oppose it. However, like Monzaemon, if nothing is pulling its strings, then it is nothing but an ornament.

Name: Ezreal
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Magic, potentially Low 6-B with Ne'Zuk's Gauntlet | Unknown, 4-B with Magic | Unknown, 7-B with Magic, 2-A via hax, up to Low 1-C | 4-B

Name: Felix (Golden Sun)
Summary: Felix is the older brother of Jenna and a native of Vale. He was thought to have died many years ago when a catastrophe had struck Vale, but he was rescued by Saturos and Menardi. He is the protagonist of Golden Sun: Lost Age. Felix set off on another journey after the Golden Sun event, and nobody has seen him since.

Name: Flash (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Bartholomew Henry Allen, or better known as Barry Allen, is the second Flash, one of DC's most iconic superheroes.

Name: Frankenstein (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Doctors... ever the same. "This is impossible", "That is impossible". Ever you register your surprise while you remain blind to the truth. NOTHING IS IMPOSSIBLE! You will show me where my companions are kept. You will show me how to release them. Or you will die the painful death of the wicked. ... Doctors.

Name: Frozomon
Summary: Frozomon is a Machine Digimon that inhabits areas with heavy snowfall and removes snow vigorously. Contrary to its reliable side that rescues those who get lost in snowstorms and the like, it is also a troublesome Digimon who uses all its strength to eliminate those that get in the way of its rescues, even if they are Babies. It is a specialist when it comes to cold regions who is capable of not only removing snow, but also melting ice with its red-hot sword.

Name: Future Flash (New 52)
Summary: Future Flash, otherwise known as The Flash or Barry Allen, is the primary antagonist of the "Out of Time" storyline.

Name: Galacta
Summary: Galacta is the estranged daughter of the Devourer of Worlds, Galactus, who has been living on Earth as a human teenage under the alias of Gali. Like her father, she possesses a cosmic hunger that can only be satisfied through the consumption of whole worlds, but unlike her father, she desires only to live a peaceful, normal life, and so has attempted to control her insatiable hunger. She follows a strict diet, only consuming the biomass of alien lifeforms who threaten Earth, so that way she can simultaneously protect her world, and (Temporarily, barely) quench her hunger. More recently, Galacta's Cosmic Hunger has become far worse due to the presence of an endosymbiotic energy parasite within her Power Cosmic lifeform, which she dubbed the "Cosmic Tapeworm".

Name: Garet
Summary: Garet is the childhood friend of Isaac in the village of Vale. He and Isaac were attacked by Saturos and Menardi during the day that the boulder in Mt. Aleph killed Isaac's father. He travels around the world of Weyard with Isaac in order to aid him in stopping the Mars Adepts Saturos and Menardi from activating the elemental lighthouses in hopes of releasing the ultimate power of alchemy.

Name: General Zod (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Genaral Zod is a former Kryptonian military general who was exiled to the Phantom Zone for treason. Following Krypton's destruction Zod and fellow exiled Kryptonian Ursa along with their son, Lor-Zod, escaped the Phantom Zone and launched an attack on the Earth city Metropolis in search of Jor-El's son, Kal-El. However, after Superman allied with Lex Luthor he foiled Zod's plan and Zod has been an enemy of Superman ever since.

Name: General Zod (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Prisoners, you have been found guilty. By order of the council, you will be exiled forever to the Phantom Zone. Do you have any final words before execution of your sentence? Zod: My name is Zod. And no matter what you do, no matter where you send me-- I promise you this. I... Will always... Be your monster. As the Phantom zone takes me, I see your faces. And I know you understand. I will turn your fear into action. I will show you all that you are capable of. I will make you great. And because of me... You will have the chance to survive... And grow strong.

Name: Grail (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: At the same time Diana was born to Hippolyta, the Amazonian assassin Myrina secretly gave birth to Darkseid's daughter, with the assistance of Penelope and under the watchful gaze of the oracle Menalippe. Upon the child’s birth, named Grail, Myrina fiercely protected her from Penelope, who had learned of a prophecy from Menalippe foretelling the destruction Grail would bring as she grew. In the aftermath, Myrina killed Menalippe and fled Themyscira with her daughter, becoming the first Amazons to ever leave the island. Decades later, Grail formed an alliance with the Anti-Monitor and assisted him in waging war against her father, Darkseid.

Name: GranKuwagamon

Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: GRB 221009A
Summary: A gamma-ray burst (GRB) is a cosmic event characterized by the sudden release of an immense amount of gamma-ray radiation. It occurs during the collapse of a massive star or the collision of neutron stars. These bursts are among the most energetic events in the universe and can last from milliseconds to several minutes, traveling nearly at the speed of light.

Name: Green Lantern (Hal Jordan)
Summary: In brightest day, in blackest night, No evil shall escape my sight. Let those who worship evil's might, Beware my power, Green Lantern's light!

Name: Green Lantern (Kyle Rayner) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Kyle Rayner is a top member of the Green Lantern Corps from Earth. After the rest of the Corps was destroyed, he alone was selected to bear the last power ring and carry on the title. Although he acted alone for many years, when the Corps was reformed, his skill level gave him a position as an Honor Guard, only behind Salakk and the Guardians in the chain of command of the Corps. He has also been a host for the Ion entity and a member of the Justice League.

Name: Grumblemon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher, 1-C with Nega Cave

Name: Gryphomon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C

Name: Guhnash
Summary: A planet eating abomination that consumed the Dinaurians home world. A living weapon that can fight with every part of its body, including internal organs, it was called to Earth by the 4 idolcomps but was killed by Hunter.

Name: Hackmon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Hagurumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | 6-B | At least High 4-C, possibly 4-A | 3-C

Name: Hangyomon
Summary: Hangyomon is an Aquatic Beast Man Digimon clothed in a wetsuit. It has a cheerful personality, and is always swimming around the "Net Ocean". Its specialty is moving in the water, and in battle it uses the high-speed, underwater mobility Motor on its back, and uses a fighting style that capitalizes on its speed.

Name: Hawkgirl (Kendra Saunders) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Kendra Saunders, Hawkgirl, is the reincarnation of Shrra, an angel cursed by her God to reincarnate across space and time alongside Kthar Deathbringer, who now combats evil as Hawkman. Born despite another Hawkwoman's existence because of Perpetua not wanting her to be whole, Kendra has proved herself a valiant hero among the ranks of the Justice League.

Name: Hawkman (Carter Hall) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: I am Carter Hall. I am Hawkman. I am an archaeologist. A scholar and preservationist of history. More than that, I am history. I've reincarnated across time, stretching back to the dawn of man. I ruled as an ancient Egyptian prince. Battled as a medieval knight. Dueled as an Old West gunhand. Yet lately, I'm plagued by the thought that the subject I know the least about is myself. That pieces of my history are missing. There remains only one truth that I know to be certain -- I am made to soar. I can't remember a life when I wasn't enthralled by flight. Open skies. Then why do I spend so much time underground? Darkness. Suffocating spaces. It's because the past is buried. And I'm swept up in the pursuit of it like a sparrow in a gale. Driven by the twin compulsions of my existence. Exploration and discovery.

Name: Hawkman (Katar Hol) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Katar Hol, known to the public as Hawkman, is a Thanagarian refugee who escaped his planet after accidentally killing his adopted brother, the prince of Thanagar. Bonded with the Nth Metal that his armor and metal are made of, Katar has been a powerful asset to the Justice League of America.

Name: Hawkwoman (Shayera Thal) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Shayera Thal, Hawkwoman, is the empress of Thanagar and wife of Carter Hall.

Name: Hecarim
Summary: Hecarim is an armored colossus who charges from the Shadow Isles at the head of a deathly host of spectral horsemen to hunt the living. A monstrous fusion of man and beast, cursed to ride for eternity, Hecarim revels in slaughter and crushing souls beneath his armored hooves.

Name: Hexeblaumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C

Name: HiAndromon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: High Evolutionary
Summary: Herbert Edgar Wyndham is a scientist obsessed with his research regarding the process of evolution, including by greatly enhancing his own intellect, by evolving animals into his servants, the noble New Men, and by creating the planet Counter-Earth, which he tried to turn into a paradise.

Name: Highfather
Summary: Highfather is one of the most powerful New Gods and the benevolent ruler of New Genesis, an archetypal world beyond the bounds of time and space.

Name: Hookmon
Summary: Hookmon is a pirate Digimon with one eye. It ventures the "Net Ocean" pursuing the phantom White Whamon, and is a courageous man of the ocean that faces up even to rough seas. Its right hand has become a hook-shaped claw, and once it has ensnared its prey, it won't let go at any cost.

Name: Hououmon
Summary: Its Special Move "Starlight Explosion" has become even more powerful due to the increase in its holy power.

Name: I, Vampire (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: What manner of witchcraft has taken me? How did I get here? And how do I live? My mind is cleared, only hunger to fill it. But a hunger like one I have never felt... It boils and seethes, like an angry dog seethes. It overwhelms, my eyes filled with one need. What is happening to me, Lord? Please speak... I feel so strange, as if I'd never lived... As though the air I breathe, the light I see, Is the first I e'er have breathed or seen. And yet, I feel a dourness awash me. As though I've lost something more than sacred. Perchance a dream where reflections aren't cast. Where good people drink blood and hunger for death-- And when prey is near, I both lay and lie-- so easily, like to this I was born.

Name: Indramon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Horse. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Zhuqiaomon, it has an intolerably arrogant personality. When it opens its mouth only bragging comes out, and it is constantly fussing over the glossiness of its mane and tail. It indulges in its talents, and ridicules those who work hard. Among the Deva, it is on especially bad terms with Vajramon. Though it fusses over its appearance, in battle it is comparatively unrefined; using the gigantic Bǎo Bèi trumpet shell tied to its arms, it beats the opponent down by wielding it like a cudgel.

Name: Infinity Gauntlet (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Infinity Stones are the condensed remains of six Singularities that existed long before the current universe. Every Stone holds a power so vast that it lies beyond mortal comprehension. Each controls a primordial aspect of the universe: space, reality, time, power, mind, and soul.

Name: Iron Man (Super Hero Squad)
Summary: nan

Name: Isaac (Golden Sun)
Summary: Isaac is the main protagonist of the first Golden Sun game. He lives in Vale, where his childhood friends, Garet and Jenna, reside. One day, a terrible storm appeared in the village (which was caused by Saturos and Menardi by accident), and resulted in the death of Isaac's father and Jenna's family. Three years later, he traveled up to Mt. Aleph, where the source of Alchemy resides with his friends and Mr. Kraden. While exploring the mountain, they come across an ancient room where the 4 elemental stars reside. Saturos, Menardi, and Jenna's supposedly deceased brother Felix followed them to the mountain, forcing them to hand over the elemental stars with the exception of the Mars Star. With Garet at his side, Isaac travels across the world of Weyard to save Jenna, and stop the evil Mars Adepts from activating the forbidden power of Alchemy. Credit to Nibroc-Rock for the Isaac render.

Name: Janna
Summary: Tier: Varies from 7-B to 4-B | 4-B

Name: Jax (League of Legends)
Summary: Runeterra’s greatest weapons master, Jax is the only survivor of the Kohari—champions sworn to the defense of Icathia. But when the Void was unleashed against the Shuriman empire’s Ascended Host, Icathia was destroyed, leaving Jax without a home or purpose. He gathered the “last light of Icathia”, a symbol of his hope to one day defeat the Void, and now travels the world, searching for warriors strong enough to face the coming darkness by his side.

Name: Jessica Cruz (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Jessica Cruz inherited the ring of the Crime Syndicate's Power Ring, becoming the new Power Ring briefly before becoming another Green Lantern of Earth. The sworn protector of Sector 2814, the power ring-bearing girl has conquered her fears and brought renewed honor to the Green Lantern Corps.

Name: Jinx (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Weapons | 5-C, 5-B with the Morning Star | 4-B

Name: John Constantine (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: John Constantine, sometimes known as The Hellblazer, is an occult detective and scammer from Liverpool. Despite him having good intentions and typically wishing to protect the world, John's extreme methods have often put him at odds with other heroes: John is a very pragmatic man, and is willing to sacrifice others to save more, or even to protect himself, though it greatly hurts him to do so.

Name: JumboGamemon
Summary: A gigantic Cyborg Digimon that added beam cannons to its entire body until the strength of its Metal Body's shell was compromised.

Name: Justimon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Kai'Sa
Summary: Claimed by the Void when she was only a child, Kai'Sa managed to survive through sheer tenacity and strength of will. Her experiences have made her a deadly hunter and, to some, the harbinger of a future they would rather not live to see. Having entered into an uneasy symbiosis with a living Void carapace, the time will soon come when she must decide whether to forgive those mortals who would call her a monster, and defeat the coming darkness together... or simply to forget, as the Void consumes the world that left her behind.

Name: Kaine Parker
Summary: Kaine was the Jackal's first attempt at cloning Peter Parker, but he was left deformed by a flaw in the cloning process and quickly became unstable.

Name: Kamen Rider OOO
Key: '''Eiji Hino''' | '''The Revival of Greeed, the Birth of OOO, and the Scramble of Medals (Episodes 1-16)''' | '''The Man of One Hundred Million, the Other Ankh, and the Purple Medals (Episodes 17-38)''' | '''The Bond of Allies, the End of the World, and the Greed Towards Tomorrow (Episodes 39-48)''' | '''Post-Series''' | '''Heisei Generations FINAL''' | '''OOO 10th: Core Medal of Resurrection'''
Summary: Eiji Hino (火野 映司, Hino Eiji?) is the main protagonist of Kamen Rider OOO. He is a 21-year-old homeless traveller who was the son of a politician. When traveling to Africa, he befriended a little girl named Ruu and attempted to use his fortune to help her struggling village. Unfortunately, this would drag Eiji into the civil war that this village was involved in. During the situation, he failed to save Ruu from being tragically killed. Eiji was then held for ransom which his parents ended up paying for, as well as using the situation as a means to gain support for their public platform.

Name: Karma (League of Legends)
Summary: No mortal exemplifies the spiritual traditions of Ionia more than Karma. She is the living embodiment of an ancient soul reincarnated countless times, carrying all her accumulated memories into each new life, and blessed with power that few can comprehend. She has done her best to guide her people in recent times of crisis, though she knows that peace and harmony may come only at a considerable cost—both to her, and to the land she holds most dear.

Name: Katana (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Tatsu Yamashiro, known as Katana, is a Japanese superhero skilled in swordsmanship. She has been a member of the Suicide Squad, the Outsiders, the Justice League of America, and the Birds of Prey. Her signature weapon, the "Soultaker" sword, is believed to trap the souls of those it slays—including her own husband.

Name: Kayle
Summary: Born to a Targonian Aspect at the height of the Rune Wars, Kayle honored her mother’s legacy by fighting for justice on wings of divine flame. She and her twin sister Morgana were the protectors of Demacia for many years—until Kayle became disillusioned with the repeated failings of mortals, and abandoned this realm altogether. Still, legends are told of her punishing the unjust with her fiery swords, and many hope that she will one day return…

Name: Kayn
Key: '''Base/Shadow Assassin''' | '''Rhaast''' | '''Odyssey Kayn''' | '''Dark Star Rhaast''' | '''Cosmic Emperor Shadow Assassin'''
Summary: A peerless practitioner of lethal shadow magic, Shieda Kayn battles to achieve his true destiny—to one day lead the Order of the Shadow into a new era of Ionian supremacy. He audaciously wields the sentient darkin weapon Rhaast, undeterred by its creeping corruption of his body and mind. There are only two possible outcomes: either Kayn bends the weapon to his will... or the malevolent blade consumes him completely, paving the way for the destruction of all Runeterra.

Name: Khonshu (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Khonshu is the Egyptian God of the Moon and Vengeance.

Name: Kirika Akatsuki
Summary: Kirika Akatsuki (暁 切歌 Akatsuki Kirika) is one of the six main characters of the Senki Zesshō Symphogear series.

Name: Kree (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Kree is an alien species originally from planet Hala, but conquered worlds all over their own galaxy becoming a giant empire. At some point they built the super computer Supreme Intelligence, which ended up becoming a ruler that they workship as a god. Kree give a great value to technology, which they have evolved leaps and bounds since their creation, because of constant wars with other races specially the Skrulls their military power increases the most. Power is also greatly valued among the race which meant making their military ranks based on individual power. At some point Kree reached a stagnation point in their evolution which the Supreme intelligence tried to fix by exploding a Nega-Bomb killing 90% of the Kree.

Name: Kumamon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C, higher with human potential | At least 3-C, Possibly higher, 1-C with Plasma Double Tomahawk| 1-C

Name: Kumbhiramon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Rat. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Xuanwumon, who boasts of its great wisdom, it is a sage who plays the part of the "challenger" in Xuanwumon's Zen Kōans. With the psychology of anyone but Xuanwumon, it is mostly able to see ahead, and has a habit of bewildering the opponent by announcing their next move. Though it uses sarcasm with an acrimonious tone, it charmingly ends all of its sentences with "~chū". As it's not very strong, it's not suited for flinging itself at the opponent, but by means of its powerful abilities of telekinesis, it freely operates a giant steel pestle as big as its own body, the Bǎo Chǔ.

Name: Lady Devimon
Summary: Lady Devimon is a Fallen Angel Digimon of noble presence and it is a minor antagonist in Digimon Adventure 01, Adventure 02, and Digimon Xros Wars, in Adventure 01 it started out as one of the servants of Piedmon.

Name: Lauri-Ell the Accuser
Summary: Lauri-Ell the Accuser, a Kree soldier born in a laboratory to be the best Kree soldier. She was born from the DNA of Mari-Ell, Carol Danvers mother, with another powerful Kree soldier, making her half-sister of Carol Danvers. After clearing her name for the explosion of the city K'in-Al she become the new accuser for Emperor Hulkling's Kree/Skrull Alliance.

Name: Leomon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Leona
Summary: Imbued with the fire of the sun, Leona is a warrior templar of the Solari who defends Mount Targon with her Zenith Blade and Shield of Daybreak. Her skin shimmers with starfire while her eyes burn with the power of the celestial Aspect within her. Armored in gold and bearing a terrible burden of ancient knowledge, Leona brings enlightenment to some, death to others.

Name: Lex Luthor (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Lex Luthor appears as a representative the government has recruited to investigate and bring down Superman. Based on background signage seen throughout the New 52 books (including Justice League), LexCorp also exists. In Justice League No. 2, Batman notes that he and Superman have at least one thing in common: both of them speak openly of their distaste for Luthor. In the New 52 Action Comics (a series set some time before the events of Justice League #1), Luthor is hired by General Sam Lane to capture Superman by setting a train accident as a trap for him. The younger Superman, who is weaker and inexperienced, barely stops the train and is left unconscious. Lex collects Superman and subjects him to a series of tests to ascertain his strengths and weaknesses. He tortures Superman until the latter manages to escape. Lex is later revealed to have obtained contact with the "Collector of Worlds" through unknown means and was told to say the word "Krypton" to Superman. He later appears when the Collector abducts New Troy as one of the residents in the area. He along with Lois and Jimmy go into Glen Glenmorgan's hotel where Lex calls the Collector and it is revealed that Lex had made a deal with him. It is later revealed that Lex Luthor was the secret caller named "Icarus" that was giving secret information on Glen Glenmorgan to Clark Kent.

Name: Lissandra
Summary: As the reclusive leader of the Frostguard, many believe Lissandra is a living saint whose followers bring healing and wisdom to the tribes of the Freljord. The truth is perhaps more sinister, as she uses her elemental magic to twist the power of True Ice into something dark and terrible, entombing or impaling any who would reveal her deepest secrets. Indeed, the legacy of her past may yet be the beginning of the end for Runeterra.

Name: LoaderLiomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B, occasionally High 8-C with Shippo Binta | High 8-C, occasionally 6-C with Critical Bite | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C

Name: Loma Shade (DC Comics)
Summary: Part of the Avian an alien race enslaved on the planet Meta, Loma Shade named herself after her favorite poet, Rac Shade, whose work could give her some much-needed escapism from her grim condition. Still inspired by his poems, Loma managed to get her hands on Rac's famous M-Vest, which transmitted her consciousness in the body of a comatose, brain-dead teenager named Megan Boyer. Loma took over her life, struggling to deal with her new abilities, the human lifestyle she was forced into and the consequences Megan's abuse of her classmates.

Name: Lulu (League of Legends)
Summary: The yordle mage Lulu is known for conjuring dreamlike illusions and fanciful creatures as she roams Runeterra with her fairy companion Pix. Lulu shapes reality on a whim, warping the fabric of the world, and what she views as the constraints of this mundane, physical realm. While others might consider her magic at best unnatural, and at worst dangerous, she believes everyone could use a touch of enchantment.

Name: Lux
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | Low 7-C | At least Low 7-C, likely far higher | 4-B | Low 1-C, higher with Final Spark | At least Low 1-C

Name: Madame Xanadu (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Madame Xanadu is an immortal sorceress with great skill in seeing the future. Thanks to this ability, she was the one to put together the team known as the Justice League Dark, to stop the Enchantress from destroying the world.

Name: Makuramon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Monkey. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Baihumon, it has a curious disposition of not speaking and not showing its emotions on its face. However, contrasted with its facial expressions, its body movements are overflowing and its emotions are expressed through its bodily poses. Those suggest that it is often in a more or less good mood, but that its overflowing curiosity doesn't last very long. It makes a hobby out of collecting and locking up the things that catch its eye in its Bǎo Yù, and in battle, it is a pacifist that locks up the opponent to settle its issues.

Name: Malcolm Graves
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | Low 7-C | 4-B

Name: Malekith (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Malekith is the primary antagonist of Thor: The Dark World. He is the leader of the Dark Elves of Svartalfheim, having led them into battle against King Bor and the Asgardians five thousand years ago. At the end of that conflict, he and his race were defeated and entered a state of suspended animation within one of their warships until the Aether resurfaced, awakening them. Malekith and the Dark Elves sacked Asgard in their quest to reclaim the Aether and use its reality-warping power together with the phenomenon known as the Convergence to transform all matter in the universe into dark matter. However, despite Malekith's best efforts, the Dark Elves were again defeated by Thor and his companions.

Name: Malzahar
Summary: A zealous seer dedicated to the unification of all life, Malzahar truly believes the newly emergent Void to be the path to Runeterra’s salvation. In the desert wastes of Shurima, he followed the voices that whispered in his mind, all the way to ancient Icathia. Amidst the ruins of that land, he gazed into the dark heart of the Void itself, and was gifted new power and purpose. Malzahar now sees himself as a shepherd, empowered to bring others into the fold...or to release the voidling creatures that dwell beneath.

Name: Mammothmon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Marin Devimon
Summary: A dirty fighter that even Devimon hates to fight. Though it is a subspecies of Devimon, it completely lacks all emotions but hatred due to its lonely life in the ocean depths. In order to win by any means, it won't let up with its attacks even if the opponent loses their fighting spirit. The two tentacles growing from its back each possess their own will, so they will struggle for the catch and act without permission.

Name: Martian Manhunter (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: J'onn J'onzz is the Martian Manhunter, one of the last survivors of the planet Mars who came to Earth in search of justice and peace. Roughly one million years ago, Mars was a living world, populated by a race of humanoids divided by skin color.

Name: MasterTyranomon
Summary: MasterTyrannomon is a Dinosaur type Digimon whose name is derived from the term "Master Tyrannomon". It is a Tyrannomon who is a veteran of many battles and evolved as a result.

Name: Max (Sharkboy and Lavagirl)
Summary: Max is a fictional character who appears as the main protagonist of the movie The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl. He is a lonely boy who uses his dreams to escape reality. He records these dreams in his Dream Journal which was given to him by his grandfather. Max as the Daydreamer is the most powerful person on Planet Drool. Sharkboy and Lavagirl try to help Max remember this as he is the only one who can save Planet Drool.

Name: Meicoomon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C, far higher with Cursed Claws | At least Low 1-C | 1-C | 1-C

Name: Mephistomon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C, Possibly 1-C

Name: Meramon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Mercuremon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher, 1-C after analyzing abilities of other legendary warriors | 1-C

Name: MetalPhantomon
Summary: Tier: Unknown, up to 6-C | 6-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C

Name: Mewtwo
Summary: Mewtwo is a Psychic-type Legendary Pokémon. The story of Mewtwo has quite a few versions, but they all start off the same. Before Mewtwo, there was Mew, the ancestor of all Pokémon.

Name: Mind Flayer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mind Flayers are horrific, eldritch creatures associated with the dark depths of the D&D settings. They are renowned for being horrendously evil and for their mental capacities. Mind Flayers thrive by devouring the minds of other creatures, generally only interacting with other species at all to eat them or to enslave their kind.

Name: Miss Fortune (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 4-B | 4-B | 4-B

Name: Mogo the Living Planet
Summary: Mogo is sentient, living planet and member of the Green Lantern Corps. He is frequently shown changing foliage on his surface into a green band that forms the Corps symbol around his equatorial area.

Name: Monica Rambeau (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Monica Rambeau is the daughter of Maria Rambeau, who was a close friend of Carol Danvers. After the Blip, she became a captain at S.W.OR.D to investigate the Westview Anomaly, which was later revealed to originate from Wanda Maximoff. She was tasked to inspect the anomaly alongside with Jimmy Woo. However, as she approached the anomaly, she was pulled inside the pocket reality and was forcibly given the role of "Geraldine." As a result of coming into contact of the Hex, her genes were rewritten, and she had gained the power to manipulate energy.

Name: Monzaemon
Summary: Tier: Unknown, Up to 6-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C, Low 1-C evolved from Numemon | Low 1-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C

Name: Moon Knight (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Steven Grant: Oh, God. I'm gonna die, I'm gonna die. Marc Spector: Steven, LOOK at me... you're not gonna die. Let me save us.

Name: Mordekaiser
Summary: Tier: At least Low 6-B, possibly 4-B | 7-A | High 6-A | 4-B | Low 1-C

Name: Morgana (League of Legends)
Summary: Conflicted between her celestial and mortal natures, Morgana bound her wings to embrace humanity, and inflicts her pain and bitterness upon the dishonest and the corrupt. She rejects laws and traditions she believes are unjust, and fights for truth from the shadows of Demacia—even as others seek to repress it—by casting shields and chains of dark fire. More than anything else, Morgana truly believes that even the banished and outcast may one day rise again.

Name: Ms. Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kamran: Look at everything I've done, Kamala. What am I supposed to do now? How can I be normal? Ms. Marvel: There is no normal. There's just us and what we do with what we've been given.

Name: Naomi (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Naomi McDuffie is a young woman born in a strange world torn apart by a war of super-powered individuals. The daughter of a couple who were apart of the original 29 given powers, Naomi was one of the only survivors of this conflict and was brought up on Prime Earth by her adoptive parents.

Name: Nasus
Summary: Nasus is an imposing, jackal-headed Ascended being from ancient Shurima, a heroic figure regarded as a demigod by the people of the desert. Fiercely intelligent, he was a guardian of knowledge and peerless strategist whose wisdom guided the ancient empire of Shurima to greatness for many centuries. After the fall of the empire, he went into self-imposed exile, becoming little more than a legend. Now that the ancient city of Shurima has risen once more, he has returned, determined to ensure it never falls again.

Name: Neeko
Summary: Hailing from a long lost tribe of vastaya, Neeko can blend into any crowd by borrowing the appearances of others, even absorbing something of their emotional state to tell friend from foe in an instant. No one is ever sure where—or who—Neeko might be, but those who intend to do her harm will soon witness her true colors revealed, and feel the full power of her primordial spirit magic unleashed upon them.

Name: Nightmare Nurse (DC Comics)
Summary: Asa, The Nightmare Nurse is a demonic being who nonetheless seeks to heal and protect humanity, though it is unknown how much of this is due to the Hippocrates Oath she is bound to. Regardless, she has helped the Justice League Dark, and more recently betrayed the Suicide Squad she was enrolled in to try and protect Swamp Thing from Amanda Waller's plans.

Name: Odin (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Odin Borson was the King of Asgard, protector of the Nine Realms, father of Hela Odinsdottir, Thor Odinson, adoptive father of Loki Laufeyson, and husband of Frigga. During the ancient times, he was worshiped as the god of wisdom by the inhabitants of Earth. Once the greatest warrior in all the Nine Realms, over the centuries he learned how to appreciate peace, eventually banishing his own daughter to Hel when she attempted to subjugate the entire universe. When Thor almost provoked a war with the Frost Giants of Jotunheim, Odin stripped him of his powers and exiled him to Earth, leaving Loki to take the throne when Odin fell into the Odinsleep. When Thor returned and saved the Frost Giants from extinction at the hands of Loki, who seemingly lost his life during the conflict, Odin realized that Thor had proven that he would be worthy enough to take the throne of Asgard one day.

Name: Oleamon
Summary: Oleamon is an Insectivorous Plant Digimon confirmed to inhabit the forest regions of the Digital World. The scent emitted from its flower lures Insect Digimon in particular. It wraps its tongue around prey entranced by its scent to taste them, and then preys on them with its "Jameal", in which it spreads its petals wide. The Digimon that it preys upon are slowly digested and become its nourishment. Oleamon, who mingles with and lives among other Plant Digimon, is a very terrifying being to Insect Digimon that coexist in the same area.

Name: Ophiuchus Supercluster Eruption
Summary: This extremely powerful eruption occurred in the Ophiuchus Supercluster, which is located about 390 million light-years from Earth. According to NASA, the Ophiuchus Supercluster eruption was the biggest and most energetic event ever recorded in the observable universe.

Name: Orion (DC Comics)
Summary: Orion, the Dog of War, is one of, if not the most powerful warriors of New Genesis, standing alongside Highfather and Darkseid as the strongest of the New Gods. From birth he was prophesied to kill Darkseid in final battle, and although they were both killed in the events preceding Final Crisis, it is unknown if that battle truly fulfilled the prophecy or not.

Name: Ornn
Summary: Ornn is the Freljordian demi-god of forging and craftsmanship. He works in the solitude of a massive smithy, hammered out from the lava caverns beneath the volcano Hearth-Home. There he stokes bubbling cauldrons of molten rock to purify ores and fashion items of unsurpassed quality. When other deities—especially Volibear—walk the earth and meddle in mortal affairs, Ornn arises to put these impetuous beings back in their place, either with his trusty hammer or the fiery power of the mountains themselves.

Name: Paildramon
Key: '''Paildramon''' | '''Imperialdramon Dragon Mode''' | '''Imperialdramon Dragon Mode (Black)''' | '''Imperialdramon Fighter Mode'''/'''Fighter Mode (Black)''' | '''Imperialdramon Paladin Mode'''
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Likely Low 1-C | 1-C | 1-C | 1-C, higher with Giga Death | At least 1-C, High 1-C with All Delete

Name: Pajiramon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Sheep. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Zhuqiaomon, it is a powerful figure who rules the world of dreams. It doesn't befriend the other Deva and is always calm, never changing its mind. Among the Deva, it has surprisingly many secrets whose truth is not divulged, and it is also known as the Dark Deva. Its personality is cruel, and lacks feelings of consideration for others. The arrows of light fired off from its Bǎo Gōng, which it never parts with even for a moment, have the power to knock out the opponent.

Name: Pantheon
Summary: Tier: 4-B, higher with Mortal Will | 4-B | Unknown, higher with Mortal Will | Unknown, higher with Mortal Will, Low 2-C with Hax

Name: Papa Midnite (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: A powerful Vodou bokor who has created his own criminal empire, Papa Midnite is one of John Constantine's most noteworthy antagonists, having been at different times his ally or sworn enemy.

Name: Pharaohmon
Summary: Tier: At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C | 1-C

Name: Phelesmon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Piccolomon
Summary: A Fairy Digimon that is fluent in magic. It can recite the advanced programming language of another dimension, allowing it to generate miracles with the appearance of magic. This miraculous Digimon is able to pop up in every place, time, and space, and although its body is small, it can seal away the enemy's abilities with its own special ability, and then pulverize the opponent with a mighty blow. With its mischief-loving personality, it enjoys making computers run wild with its cherished spear, "Fairy Tale", that it always holds in its hands (although it has no ill intent).

Name: Poppy
Summary: Tier: 9-A | 4-B

Name: Power Girl (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Kara Zor-L was among the sole survivors of Krypton's last days. Rocketed into space, she was found by the kind-hearted Superman, who raised her as if she were his own daughter. As Supergirl, she was a juvenile hero who unfortunately lost her innocence in the Apokolips War, which would eventually destroy all of Earth. Sent through a portal to the "Prime Earth" of Earth 0, Kara took up the identity of Power Girl.

Name: Professor Zoom (New 52)
Summary: Eobard Thawne, also known as Professor Zoom, is the archenemy of Barry Allen. Born in the 25th century, Thawne became resentful towards the world after he witnessed his father inexplicably murder his mother. After being struck by a mysterious bolt of lightning he gained the power to slow down time around him which he used, combined with his resentment, to conquer the Gem Cities, however even with to threat of death lying at the citizens of the cities, they refused to give in, in the name of their hero and idol: The Flash. Infuriated by this, Zoom would travel back in time to recruit allies with distinct Speed Force-derived abilities to slowly break down and poison the legacy of Barry Allen.

Name: Pumpkinmon
Summary: Pumpkinmon is a plush toy Digimon with a pumpkin head. There's an urban legend that says Pumpmon came to be when mutations developed in a computer virus created during the season of the Western holiday of "Halloween". However, though it doesn't inflict any harm at all because it was not a malignant virus, its external appearance belies its possession of powerful offensive ability. As you can tell even from looking at its blank face, a rare expression of emotions is characteristic of Puppet Digimon.

Name: Qiyana
Summary: In the jungle city of Ixaocan, Qiyana plots her own ruthless path to the high seat of the Yun Tal. Last in line to succeed her parents, she faces those who stand in her way with brash confidence and unprecedented mastery over elemental magic. With the land itself obeying her every command, Qiyana sees herself as the greatest elementalist in the history of Ixaocan—and by that right, deserving of not only a city, but an empire.

Name: Quantum Bands (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Quantum Bands are ancient artifacts of the Kree, that are made out of Noor, an energy source used by the Noor Dimension. The bands created the Universal Neural Teleportation Network, which is a system of every jump point existing in the universe. The bands can control the Noor and were pursued by the Clandestines so that they can return to the Noor Dimension. One of the bands was discovered by Aisha and the Clandestines who were searching for artifacts inside the Ten Rings Temple. Years later, one of the bands were bestowed to Kamala Khan and had unlocked her latent powers due to her connection to the Noor. Years after Ms. Marvel mastered her abilities, the second band was discovered in another planet by Dar-Benn who used its powers to create jump points to steal resources from other planets to restore Hala.

Name: Rac Shade (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Where dark falls dark despite the light, I touch. I smell. I breathe. I beat. Running off to the great blue. Our hearts, now lost, just fade away.

Name: Ragman (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Rory Regan is an ex-US soldier who now seemingly lives a quiet life as owner of the book/antique shop Rags 'n Tatters, but in reality lives a second life as the vigilante Ragman, who uses a demonic cloak to fight evil.

Name: Rakan
Summary: As mercurial as he is charming, Rakan is an infamous vastayan troublemaker and the greatest battle-dancer in Lhotlan tribal history. To the humans of the Ionian highlands, his name has long been synonymous with wild festivals, uncontrollable parties, and anarchic music. Few would suspect this energetic, traveling showman is also partner to the rebel Xayah, and is dedicated to her cause.

Name: Ranamon
Summary: Ranamon serves as a villain from Digimon Frontier. Cherubimon created her from the spirits of water of AncientMermaimon making her the Legendary Warrior of Water.

Name: Raven (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Raven, also known as Rachel Roth, is a superhero with dark magic powers. Her strong personal motivations and desire to do good conflict with her heritage, as her father is a powerful demon named Trigon who wants to enslave the planet. Her mother is a human woman named Arella who was living in the mystical realm of Azarath.

Name: Renekton
Summary: Renekton is a terrifying, rage-fueled Ascended being from the scorched deserts of Shurima. Once, he was his empire’s most esteemed warrior, leading the armies of Shurima to countless victories. However, after the empire’s fall, Renekton was entombed beneath the sands, and slowly, as the world turned and changed, he succumbed to insanity. Now free once more, he is utterly consumed with finding and killing his brother, Nasus, who he blames, in his madness, for the centuries he spent in darkness.

Name: Reverse Flash (Daniel West)
Summary: Daniel West is the younger brother of Iris West, whose mother died while giving birth to him. Their mother's death drives their father William to become an alcoholic and abusive towards his children, blaming Daniel for his mother's death. At the age of 12, Daniel pushes William down the stairs in response to his actions, crippling him.

Name: Rito Revolto
Summary: Rito Revolto is the brother of Rita Repulsa and the son of Master Vile. Once a "normal" villain much like his sister, everything changed after he was offered as a vessel to Dark Specter by his father, Rito failed as a vessel which resulted to his appearance being reduced to a skeleton and his mind and soul being burned in the process which made him a complete idiot

Name: Riven
Summary: Once a swordmaster in the warhosts of Noxus, Riven is an expatriate in a land she previously tried to conquer. She rose through the ranks on the strength of her conviction and her brutal efficiency, and was rewarded with a legendary runic blade—however, on the Ionian front, Riven’s faith in her homeland was tested and ultimately broken. Having severed all ties to the empire, she now wanders with her shattered sword, seeking to atone for a past she cannot fully recall.

Name: Ronan the Accuser (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ronan the Accuser is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is a judicial officer of the fictional alien race known as the Kree. Although usually portrayed as a supervillain, he is sometimes depicted as a more noble and honorable character.

Name: Ryze
Summary: Widely considered one of the most adept sorcerers on Runeterra, Ryze is an ancient, hard-bitten archmage with an impossibly heavy burden to bear. Armed with immense arcane power and a boundless constitution, he tirelessly hunts for World Runes—fragments of the raw magic that once shaped the world from nothingness. He must retrieve these glyphs before they fall into the wrong hands, for Ryze understands the horrors they could unleash on Runeterra.

Name: Sakuyamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Sandiramon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Snake. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Zhuqiaomon, it is the most cunning and cruel among the Deva. It doesn't like to decide matches in an instant, and prefers to instead choke the life out of the opponent while tormenting them bit by bit. It usually lives deep beneath the ground, and subterranean maneuvers are its specialty. During battle, it can produce a spear made of light, the Bǎo Kuí, from its mouth, and skillfully wield it with its tail wrapped around it like a hand. Although the Bǎo Kuí vanishes once it slashes the opponent, as long as Sandiramon's energy lasts, it can spit out any number of them, and they will not degrade in sharpness.

Name: Scorpiomon
Summary: A computer virus infected the databanks of a laboratory where the investigations and excavations of ancient life forms is performed, and took in the data of an ancient life form and evolved. It became like the life form which in ancient times was the apex of the food chain, which had a great appetite and supplied it with an ability capable of allowing it to see food that was of the finest quality. Skillfully using the tentacles that grow from its head, it catches the enemy and kills them with the sharp blade that grows from its tail. When the progression of a fight becomes disadvantageous, it uses its sharp tentacles to hoist up the soil of the seabed to hide its body. The radar eye that projects from its head captures the enemy like a night vision scope, watching for the chance to create a turnabout.

Name: Senna (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: 4-B | Unknown

Name: Shauna Vayne
Summary: Tier: 4-B | Unknown | Unknown

Name: Shiny Rod
Summary: The Claiomh Solais, named the Shiny Rod by Shiny Chariot, is a wand of legend with the power to break the seal on the Grand Triskelion. It was first obtained by Chariot before falling into the hands of Atsuko Kagari.

Name: ShogunGekomon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Sinduramon
Summary: One of the "Deva Digimon", it is a Perfect Digimon with a form resembling the Rooster. As a follower of the Four Holy Beasts Digimon Baihumon, it likes to quarrel and gossip above all else. With its provocative attitude, it will pick a fight with its opponent one way or another, but when they move to attack, it immediately draws its head and wings within its spherical armor. Its armor is the hardest among all of the Deva's equipment, and once it gets inside of the armor, it is absolutely protected. During battle, it is occasionally possible to cut through the breach when it rolls around in that state.

Name: Sirenmon
Summary: Sirenmon is a God Man Digimon which has an outward appearance like a blending of bird and fish. Its personality is cheerful, and it is always singing pleasant songs throughout the skies and seas. Its voice has a miraculously sweet sound and actually has an eight octave range from very high notes to very low notes, and it brings tranquility even to devastated battlefields with its singing voice.

Name: Sona Buvelle
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 4-B | High 6-A | 5-C

Name: Sora (Ninjago)
Summary: Sora (originally born as Ana) is the Elemental Master of Technology and a smart inventor. Born in Imperium, she was one of the smartest inventor of her Realm, but after seeing how her kingdom mistreated the dragons and being disowned by her parents, she left her home following the Merge and befriended Arin, changing her name to "Sora". She later on meet Lloyd and became one of his ninja students, eventually reaching her True Potential in a fight against the evil Empress Beatrix

Name: Soraka
Summary: A wanderer from the celestial realm, Soraka gave up her immortal form to protect the mortal races from their own ignorance and violent instincts. She endeavors to spread the virtues of compassion and mercy to everyone she meets—guiding the lost, and healing the wounded. For all Soraka has seen of this world's struggles, she still believes the people of Runeterra have yet to reach their full potential.

Name: Sphinx (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Anath-Na Mut better known as Sphinx is a recurring villain of Nova who first appeared in Nova Vol 1 6. From there on he'd proceed to also fight the likes of the Fantastic Four and the New Warriors. Anath-Na Mut was the chief wizard for Pharaoh during his reign, but after he lost the battle to Moses,[1] he was exiled from the empire. Walking the sands of Egypt for 90 years, Anath-Na Mut found the Ka Stone. Upon placing the stone on his forehead, Anath-Na Mut was forever transformed into a deathless immortal who is doomed to walk this earth forever.[2]

Name: Starfire (Post-Flasphoint)
Summary: Koriand'r, known as Starfire, is a powerful alien warrior and a key figure in DC Comics. A princess from the planet Tamaran, Koriand'r was sold into slavery by her sister Komand'r (Blackfire) to the alien race known as the Citadel. After enduring years of imprisonment and experimentation by the Psions, she escaped and eventually made her way to Earth, seeking freedom and a fresh start. In the New 52, Starfire is depicted as an independent and strong-willed individual, often teaming up with Jason Todd and Roy Harper as part of the Outlaws, and later on as part of the Titans.
