Her character balances a fierce warrior spirit with a sense of wonder and curiosity about her new home planet.

Name: Starmon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Summoners (League of Legends)
Summary: A Summoner is a term commonly used to describe a person in the League of Legends universe who primarily uses summoning magic for battle. In modern times, summoners are types of magic or non-magic users that summon minions, monsters, or structures to aid them in battle. Summoners formerly played a major role in the League of Legends universe, with all major political decisions in Valoran being decided by the outcome of the contests that take place on the Fields of Justice.

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Super-Man
Summary: Kenan Kong was an ordinary teenage school bully from Shanghai, China until one day he saved his main victim from the supervillain Blue Condor. This caught attention from China's Ministry of Self-Reliance, which was seeking recruits to create its own version of the American Justice League. He was imbued with Superman's power and became "the new Super-Man of China".

Name: Superboy (Jonathan Samuel Kent) (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jonathan Samuel "Jon" Kent is the biological son of Superman and Lois Lane. Born with the help of Thomas Wayne in the Flashpoint timeline, Jon grew up oblivious to his heritage and the fact that he and his parents were from an entirely different version of Earth than the one he lives in. However, various circumstances led him to discover his family's past and awaken his latent Kryptonian powers. As a result, his father decided to officially begin teaching Jon about his abilities, allowing him to become Superboy.

Name: Supergirl (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Supergirl is a fictional superheroine appearing in comic books published by DC Comics and related media. The character was created by writer Otto Binder and designed by artist Al Plastino. Going by the real name Kara Zor-El, Supergirl is the biological cousin and female counterpart to DC Comic's iconic superhero Superman, created by writer Jerome Siegel and designed by artist Joseph Shuster.

Name: Superman (New 52)
Summary: Clark Kent: I can jump half a mile. I can lift a truck. I can start a fire with a stare. Pa. I wasn't there for you--I'm so sorry. Jonathan Kent: Shh! Clark! No man on Earth has the amazing powers you have. Promise me you'll use them to be a force for good--a champion of the downtrodden. Never give up the fight to make the world a better place, son...

Name: Supernova
Summary: A nova or classical nova is a transient astronomical event that causes the sudden appearance of a bright, apparently "new" star, that slowly fades over several weeks or many months. Novae involve an interaction between two stars that cause the flare-up that is perceived as a new entity that is much brighter than the stars involved. Causes of the dramatic appearance of a nova vary, depending on the circumstances of the two progenitor stars. All observed novae involve closely located binary stars (the progenitors) - either a pair of red dwarfs in the process of merging or a star and white dwarf, all considered to be cataclysmic variable stars. Luminous red novae share the name and are also cataclysmic variables, but are a different type of event caused by a stellar merger. Also with similar names are the much more energetic supernovae (SNe) and kilonovae.

Name: Swamp Thing (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Swamp Thing is an elemental creature who shares a connection to all plant life on the planet Earth through a network called the Green. He is a mass of vegetable matter that absorbed the memories and personality of Alec Holland, a botanist who died in a swamp shortly after creating a hormonal Bio-Restorative Formula for plants. He is associated with the Parliament of Trees and the White Lantern Corps. This profile is for the New 52 / Post-Flashpoint version of the character.

Name: Syndra
Summary: Syndra is a fearsome Ionian mage with incredible power at her command. As a child, she disturbed the village elders with her reckless and wild magic. She was sent away to be taught greater control, but eventually discovered her supposed mentor was restraining her abilities. Forming her feelings of betrayal and hurt into dark spheres of energy, Syndra has sworn to destroy all who would try to control her.

Name: Taric
Summary: Taric is the Aspect of the Protector, wielding incredible power as Runeterra’s guardian of life, love, and beauty. Shamed by a dereliction of duty and exiled from his homeland Demacia, Taric ascended Mount Targon to find redemption, only to discover a higher calling among the stars. Imbued with the might of ancient Targon, the Shield of Valoran now stands ever vigilant against the insidious corruption of the Void.

Name: Tenchi Masaki
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''With the Juraian armor and the Tenchi-ken''' | '''Awakened Power''' | '''New Timeline''' | '''Ascended self'''
Summary: Tenchi Masaki (柾木 天地, Masaki Tenchi) is the main protagonist of the Tenchi Muyo! series. Tenchi was a normal boy until he unsealed Ryoko Hakubi, and became the center of events surrounding the highest authority of the galaxy, Jurai. In the Ryo-Ohki continuity, he's actually the grandson of Yosho, the crown prince of Jurai as well as one of the only beings who's able to create Light Hawk Wings as a result of Tokimi's disruption of space-time in the hope of creating a being stronger than her and her sisters.

Name: Thanos (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thanos, referred to as the Dark Lord by his most loyal underlings and the Mad Titan by the galactic community, is a powerful Titan warlord who rules over a distant region of space and commands two massive armies, known as the Chitauri and the Outriders, and a small group of followers known as the Black Order whom he adopted as his children. His main objective was to bring stability from the universe, as he believed its massive population would inevitably use up the universe's resources and condemn it. However, his methodology to succeed was warped; through the use of the ancient Infinity Stones, he intended to harness their power to exterminate half of all life in the universe, thus returning it to what he perceived to be a state of cosmic balance.

Name: The Batman Who Laughs
Summary: On Earth -22, the Joker's insane rampage across Gotham City caused Batman to finally snap, breaking his long-held creed to never take a life, snapping the Clown Prince of Crime's neck to end the threat he posed once and for all. Unbeknownst to him, this released a special strain of Joker Venom that Batman inhaled, slowly twisting his moral fiber until he was no different from the Joker himself.

Name: The Bride (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: The Bride of Frankenstein was the second creation of Victor Frankenstein, meant to be a companion to his first success. While she was indeed married to Frankenstein for decades, the two split up after a traumatic incident where Frank was forced to kill their recently created, would-be son.

Name: The Dawnbreaker
Summary: With darkness black, I choke the light! No brightest day escapes my sight! I turn the dawn to midnight! Beware my power… Dawnbreaker’s might!

Name: The Devastator
Summary: On Earth -1, Superman suddenly became murderous with no discernible reason. The world's heroes held out hope that they could possibly cure Superman or break through to the man they believed he was. After weeks of this, Superman murdered his wife, Lois, and Batman had decided to stop his former friend. Ultimately, in resignation and betrayal, he infected himself with a strain of the Doomsday virus.

Name: The Drowned
Summary: My amnesty begins here. I light my signal. My light... to show this world my intent... I'm going to drown it all. This whole world. Trust me on that.

Name: The Merciless
Summary: The Merciless is an alternative version of Batman from -Earth 12 from the Dark Multiverse and one of Barbatos' Dark Knights.

Name: The Murder Machine
Summary: On Earth -44, several villains of Batman found their way into the Batcave. There, they found his loyal butler and surrogate parental figure, Alfred Pennyworth. They brutally assaulted and interrogated Alfred, demanding to know where Batman was. Loyal to the end, Alfred denied even knowing what a 'Batman' was. Ultimately, Alfred was beaten to death.

Name: The Red Death (Dark Nights Metal)
Summary: On Earth -52, Batman is battling The Flash, with the world on the verge of destruction, demanding to have the Speed Force to save his family. When outmatched, Bruce resorts to false sentiment to lure Barry Allen closer to him, proceeding to freeze his leg and swiftly knock him unconscious.

Name: The Robin King
Summary: Bruce Wayne was born into the wealthy Wayne family of Gotham City. However, he had been a violent child ever since he was a baby, which the butler Alfred Pennyworth knew but ignored out of attachment and the belief that he'll grow up to have a calmer personality. The child would make an excuse whenever he was caught, and Alfred helped hide his violent attacks even from his parents but one day decided he had enough. Unfortunately for him, that very same day Bruce killed his parents when they took him to the movie theater. They were stopped by a mugger as they were returning home, but he stabbed him before using his gun to kill his shocked parents. When the police arrived, he lied that the mugger had shot them.

Name: The Sentry (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Robert "Bob" Reynolds is a former drug addict who took part in Project Sentry, an operation by O.X.E. designed to create the ultimate superhero. Unlike the project's other test subjects, Reynolds survived the experiments and gained immense power, but he was erroneously deemed a failure and stored in the O.X.E. Vault with his memory partially wiped. He was later freed during a conflict between Yelena Belova, U.S. Agent and Ghost, and had to join forces with them to escape alive. Reynolds soon discovered his abilities and was brought before Valentina Allegra de Fontaine, who provided him with a suit and dubbed him Sentry.

Name: Tig Rafelson (DC Comics)
Summary: Tig Rafelson is a young vampire hunter who ran into Andrew Bennett, ambushing him as he searched for his wife and enemy Mary Seward. While she came close to defeating him, he convinced her to temporarily side with him. While nominally on Andrew's side, Tig would often be a wrench in his plans, even killing him at one point, and after his return, he turned her into his vampire minion while under an evil curse. Tig finally found her death at the hands of Cain, who briefly used her body to resurrect his wife Lilith, but was quickly defeated alongside her by Andrew and Mary.

Name: Trigon (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Trigon is an immensely powerful demon warlord who rules over the Under Realms. He was born of celestial blasphemy and has ruled his kingdoms since before time began. He glories in the enslavement and torture of the dimensions under his control. As Raven's father, his ultimate desire is to have Raven join him of her own free will, inheriting his kingdom and ruling by his side.

Name: Tyrannomon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least 6-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | 1-C

Name: Tyrell
Summary: Tyrell is the son of Garet and the best friend of Matthew. He is the deuteragonist of Golden Sun: Dark Dawn. He lives in a cabin built by Isaac on the Goma Plateau, a place made by the side effect of the Golden Sun event. It was through Tyrell's immaturity that the adventure between him and Matthew started, due to him using Kraden's Soarwing to fly, and crash-landing in a nearby abandoned mineshaft, waiting to be rescued. It was there that the first Psynergy Vortex was found, and Isaac and Garet sent their sons and Karis out on their quest that leads to saving Weyard.

Name: Universal Weapon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Universal Weapon, also known as Cosmi-Rod, is one of the main weapons of the Kree race, being used by powerful Kree who managed to reach the highest rank in the Kree army, Supreme Accuser. It's most commonly known wielder is Ronan the Accuser, who made multiple appearances on Earth to enforce the Kree laws using the powers of of the weapon. It's currently being wielded by Lauri-Ell that is protecting the current emperor of the Kree/Skrull alliance Dorrek-Vell.

Name: Ursa (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: nan

Name: Varus
Summary: One of the ancient race of Darkin, Varus was a deadly killer who loved to torment his foes with arrows, driving them to insanity before closing for the kill. Possessed of wondrous beauty, Varus was imprisoned at the end of the Darkin War, but escaped, centuries later, in the remade flesh of two Ionian hunters. The two men had unwittingly released Varus and now bear the bow containing his bound essence. Varus now hunts those who trapped him in order to enact his brutal vengeance, but the souls bound within him fight him every step of the way.

Name: Viego
Summary: Once ruler of a long-lost kingdom, Viego perished over a thousand years ago when his attempt to bring his wife back from the dead triggered the magical catastrophe known as the Ruination. Transformed into a powerful, unliving wraith tortured by an obsessive longing for his centuries-dead queen, Viego now stands as the Ruined King, controlling the deadly Harrowings as he scours Runeterra for anything that might one day restore her, and destroying all in his path as the Black Mist pours endlessly from his cruel, broken heart.

Name: Volibear
Summary: To those who still revere him, the Volibear is the storm made manifest. Destructive, wild, and stubbornly resolute, he existed before mortals walked the Freljord's tundra, and is fiercely protective of the lands that he and his demi-god kin created. Cultivating a deep hatred of civilization and the weakness it brought with it, he now fights to return to the old ways—when the land was untamed, and blood spilled freely—and eagerly battles all who oppose him, with tooth, claw, and thundering domination.

Name: WarGreymon
Summary: An ultimate form of Greymon-species Digimon, it is a subspecies of War Greymon armed with electric-powered weapons.

Name: Wisemon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C

Name: Witchmon
Summary: Tier: 6-C, 3-C on Halloween | At least 4-C, possibly 3-C, far higher on Halloween

Name: Wonder Woman (Golden Age)
Summary: Tier: 4-C

Name: Wonder Woman (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Wonder Woman is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics. The character is a demigoddess and warrior princess of the Amazons (who are based on the Amazons of Greek mythology) and is known in her homeland as Princess Diana of Themyscira.

Name: Xayah
Summary: Deadly and precise, Xayah is a vastayan revolutionary waging a personal war to save her people. She uses her speed, guile, and razor-sharp feather blades to cut down anyone who stands in her way. Xayah fights alongside her partner and lover, Rakan, to protect their dwindling tribe, and restore their race to her vision of its former glory.

Name: Xenagos
Summary: Xenagos is renowned for his satyr charisma and ability to whip revelers into a frenzy. But will his endless pursuit of pleasure lead to godlike ambitions? For the satyrs of the Skola Valley on Theros, pleasure, revelry, and mischief are virtues of the highest regard. Xenagos is the epitome of these ideals. While he does not rule the satyrs, Xenagos savors his role as de facto revelry host. When his Planeswalker spark ignited, he was excited to bring his boisterous, carefree hedonism to distant planes. His goal was to discover all the pleasures of the Multiverse...but what he found instead was disillusionment. On Theros, his gods were real, but elsewhere, they held no influence. This began to gnaw at Xenagos, who ultimately returned to his home plane. While he tried to throw himself back into the revelries, they no longer gave him the same level of amusement. The natural order of things on Theros had become a farce to Xenagos, and he refused to play the fool. Where once Xenagos lived only for the moment, his newfound awareness of the Multiverse had ruined his ability to lose himself in the bedlam of satyr festivities. However, he refuses to succumb to listlessness, and just as he has been known to push revelries a few steps too far, Xenagos is now working a plan to elevate himself from mortal to god.

Name: Xerath
Summary: Xerath is an Ascended Magus of ancient Shurima, a being of arcane energy writhing in the broken shards of a magical sarcophagus. For millennia, he was trapped beneath the desert sands, but the rise of Shurima freed him from his ancient prison. Driven insane with power, he now seeks to take what he believes is rightfully his and replace the upstart civilizations of the world with one fashioned in his image.

Name: Yasuo
Summary: An Ionian of deep resolve, Yasuo is an agile swordsman, trained to wield the air itself against his enemies. As a young man, pride led him down a path of loss, costing him his position, his mentor, and ultimately his own brother. Disgraced by false accusations and now hunted as little more than a criminal, Yasuo wanders his homeland seeking redemption for his past, with only the wind to guide his blade.

Name: Zatanna (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: You want to know why I perform as a stage magician? Why my father did before me? Here's the real trick, Bruce. The secret behind it all. The more you let magic consume your life, the less connected to the real world you become. You become a ghost of yourself. You become less and less of a person. It just eats away at you, Bruce. Every day, the knowledge consumes you. Suddenly, you know that none of the laws of nature really matter. You can change all of it with a few backwards words. YTIVARG ON EROM. THGIN SEMOCEB YAD. NIAR SEMOCEB SREWOLF. And then you can put it all right back. KCAB OT LAMRON. Do you know how hard it is to talk to someone in the real world when you know that, Bruce? How hard it is to anchor yourself to the real? So maybe you force it. You keep a schedule, make yourself deal with the real people, day in, day out, so you don't forget their perspective matters as much as your own. So you stay something like a human.

Name: Ziggs
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Hexplosives, higher with Mega Inferno Bomb | 4-B | 5-C

Name: Zoe (League of Legends)
Summary: As the embodiment of mischief, imagination, and change, Zoe acts as the cosmic messenger of Targon, heralding major events that reshape worlds. Her mere presence warps the arcane mathematics governing realities, sometimes causing cataclysms without conscious effort or malice. This perhaps explains the breezy nonchalance with which Zoe approaches her duties, giving her plenty of time to focus on playing games, tricking mortals, or otherwise amusing herself. An encounter with Zoe can be joyous and life affirming, but it is always more than it appears and often extremely dangerous.

Name: Arin (Ninjago)
Summary: Arin is a self-taught Spinjitzu prodigy, creator of Object Spinjitzu, and one of Lloyd's ninja students. He is the first known person to teach himself Spinjitzu without a master. He used to live in a neighbourhood outside Ninjago City, until the Merge caused his parents and region to dissappear. Multiple years after the Merge, Arin and his best friend Sora became students of the Green Ninja Lloyd Garmadon after saving a dragon called Riyu. With the help of the other original ninja, Arin helped to free most of the dragons from Imperium. He and Lloyd searched for the Pink Dragon Core, defeat Beatrix, and helped to stabilize the Merged Realms during the MergeQuake Storm, where he saw his parents through a rift.

Name: Constellate (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Constellates are large sentient star constellations that roam the night sky. Generally peaceful and avoiding conflict, they will fight with overwhelming force if necessary. They're connected by unknown means to the Aperusa

Name: Felix (Golden Sun)
Summary: Felix is the older brother of Jenna and a native of Vale. He was thought to have died many years ago when a catastrophe had struck Vale, but he was rescued by Saturos and Menardi. He is the protagonist of Golden Sun: Lost Age. Felix set off on another journey after the Golden Sun event, and nobody has seen him since.

Name: Garet
Summary: Garet is the childhood friend of Isaac in the village of Vale. He and Isaac were attacked by Saturos and Menardi during the day that the boulder in Mt. Aleph killed Isaac's father. He travels around the world of Weyard with Isaac in order to aid him in stopping the Mars Adepts Saturos and Menardi from activating the elemental lighthouses in hopes of releasing the ultimate power of alchemy.

Name: Green Lantern (Kyle Rayner) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Kyle Rayner is a top member of the Green Lantern Corps from Earth. After the rest of the Corps was destroyed, he alone was selected to bear the last power ring and carry on the title. Although he acted alone for many years, when the Corps was reformed, his skill level gave him a position as an Honor Guard, only behind Salakk and the Guardians in the chain of command of the Corps. He has also been a host for the Ion entity and a member of the Justice League.

Name: Hagurumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | 6-B | At least High 4-C, possibly 4-A | 3-C

Name: Isaac (Golden Sun)
Summary: Isaac is the main protagonist of the first Golden Sun game. He lives in Vale, where his childhood friends, Garet and Jenna, reside. One day, a terrible storm appeared in the village (which was caused by Saturos and Menardi by accident), and resulted in the death of Isaac's father and Jenna's family. Three years later, he traveled up to Mt. Aleph, where the source of Alchemy resides with his friends and Mr. Kraden. While exploring the mountain, they come across an ancient room where the 4 elemental stars reside. Saturos, Menardi, and Jenna's supposedly deceased brother Felix followed them to the mountain, forcing them to hand over the elemental stars with the exception of the Mars Star. With Garet at his side, Isaac travels across the world of Weyard to save Jenna, and stop the evil Mars Adepts from activating the forbidden power of Alchemy. Credit to Nibroc-Rock for the Isaac render.

Name: Kamen Rider OOO
Key: '''Eiji Hino''' | '''The Revival of Greeed, the Birth of OOO, and the Scramble of Medals (Episodes 1-16)''' | '''The Man of One Hundred Million, the Other Ankh, and the Purple Medals (Episodes 17-38)''' | '''The Bond of Allies, the End of the World, and the Greed Towards Tomorrow (Episodes 39-48)''' | '''Post-Series''' | '''Heisei Generations FINAL''' | '''OOO 10th: Core Medal of Resurrection'''
Summary: Eiji Hino (火野 映司, Hino Eiji?) is the main protagonist of Kamen Rider OOO. He is a 21-year-old homeless traveller who was the son of a politician. When traveling to Africa, he befriended a little girl named Ruu and attempted to use his fortune to help her struggling village. Unfortunately, this would drag Eiji into the civil war that this village was involved in. During the situation, he failed to save Ruu from being tragically killed. Eiji was then held for ransom which his parents ended up paying for, as well as using the situation as a means to gain support for their public platform.

Name: Kirika Akatsuki
Summary: Kirika Akatsuki (暁 切歌 Akatsuki Kirika) is one of the six main characters of the Senki Zesshō Symphogear series.

Name: Mind Flayer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mind Flayers are horrific, eldritch creatures associated with the dark depths of the D&D settings. They are renowned for being horrendously evil and for their mental capacities. Mind Flayers thrive by devouring the minds of other creatures, generally only interacting with other species at all to eat them or to enslave their kind.

Name: Sora (Ninjago)
Summary: Sora (originally born as Ana) is the Elemental Master of Technology and a smart inventor. Born in Imperium, she was one of the smartest inventor of her Realm, but after seeing how her kingdom mistreated the dragons and being disowned by her parents, she left her home following the Merge and befriended Arin, changing her name to "Sora". She later on meet Lloyd and became one of his ninja students, eventually reaching her True Potential in a fight against the evil Empress Beatrix

Name: Supernova
Summary: A nova or classical nova is a transient astronomical event that causes the sudden appearance of a bright, apparently "new" star, that slowly fades over several weeks or many months. Novae involve an interaction between two stars that cause the flare-up that is perceived as a new entity that is much brighter than the stars involved. Causes of the dramatic appearance of a nova vary, depending on the circumstances of the two progenitor stars. All observed novae involve closely located binary stars (the progenitors) - either a pair of red dwarfs in the process of merging or a star and white dwarf, all considered to be cataclysmic variable stars. Luminous red novae share the name and are also cataclysmic variables, but are a different type of event caused by a stellar merger. Also with similar names are the much more energetic supernovae (SNe) and kilonovae.

Name: Tyrell
Summary: Tyrell is the son of Garet and the best friend of Matthew. He is the deuteragonist of Golden Sun: Dark Dawn. He lives in a cabin built by Isaac on the Goma Plateau, a place made by the side effect of the Golden Sun event. It was through Tyrell's immaturity that the adventure between him and Matthew started, due to him using Kraden's Soarwing to fly, and crash-landing in a nearby abandoned mineshaft, waiting to be rescued. It was there that the first Psynergy Vortex was found, and Isaac and Garet sent their sons and Karis out on their quest that leads to saving Weyard.

Name: Captain Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Captain Carol Susan Jane Danvers, also known as Captain Marvel, is a former United States Air Force pilot who, upon being exposed to the energy of the Tesseract, obtained cosmic powers. She was made into a Kree-Human hybrid via a blood transfusion from Yon-Rogg, while having her memories removed, turning her into the Kree's weapon and a member of Starforce. During the Kree's war with the Skrulls, Danvers returned to Earth and began recalling her past, with help from Nick Fury and Maria Rambeau. Danvers also discovered that Yon-Rogg had been manipulating her for years, learning from Talos that the Skrulls were merely seeking to find a new home. With this information, Danvers unlocked her true powers and defeated the Kree invasion onto Earth that was being led by Ronan the Accuser, before setting off out to the far reaches of the galaxy to finish what her late mentor Mar-Vell had once started.

Name: Dar-Benn (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Supremor Dar-Benn was a revolutionary Kree warrior and an Accuser of the Kree Empire who fought to restore her homeland after a long civil war. Formerly a member of Starforce, she blamed Captain Marvel for inciting a long civil war on Hala, which led to the planet's desolation. After discovering a Quantum Band on MB-418, Dar-Benn tore apart Jump Points in space to extract natural resources from various planets to restore her homeworld. She was eventually killed as a result of using two Quantum Bands at the same time.

Name: Monica Rambeau (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Monica Rambeau is the daughter of Maria Rambeau, who was a close friend of Carol Danvers. After the Blip, she became a captain at S.W.OR.D to investigate the Westview Anomaly, which was later revealed to originate from Wanda Maximoff. She was tasked to inspect the anomaly alongside with Jimmy Woo. However, as she approached the anomaly, she was pulled inside the pocket reality and was forcibly given the role of "Geraldine." As a result of coming into contact of the Hex, her genes were rewritten, and she had gained the power to manipulate energy.

Name: Ms. Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kamran: Look at everything I've done, Kamala. What am I supposed to do now? How can I be normal? Ms. Marvel: There is no normal. There's just us and what we do with what we've been given.

Name: Quantum Bands (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Quantum Bands are ancient artifacts of the Kree, that are made out of Noor, an energy source used by the Noor Dimension. The bands created the Universal Neural Teleportation Network, which is a system of every jump point existing in the universe. The bands can control the Noor and were pursued by the Clandestines so that they can return to the Noor Dimension. One of the bands was discovered by Aisha and the Clandestines who were searching for artifacts inside the Ten Rings Temple. Years later, one of the bands were bestowed to Kamala Khan and had unlocked her latent powers due to her connection to the Noor. Years after Ms. Marvel mastered her abilities, the second band was discovered in another planet by Dar-Benn who used its powers to create jump points to steal resources from other planets to restore Hala.

Name: Alaskan Bull Worm
Summary: nan

Name: Algol (Soul Calibur)
Summary: Algol, also known as "The Hero King," was able to obtain Soul Edge, and with his indomitable will, he resisted the sword's control. According to the legend, he used the sword to spread peace among the lands, building the Tower of Glory as a monument to his reign. His son, Arcturus, jealous of his father's power and unaware of the sword's malevolent properties, stole Soul Edge for himself and was possessed. Faced with no other choice, Algol battled and defeated his son with a fatal strike.

Name: Aura Michibane
Summary: Aura Michibane (道羽根 アウラ, Michibane Aura) the leader of a mysterious religious group in the world of the living known as Xcution. She is a fullbringer.

Name: Ayon
Summary: Ayon (アヨン, Ayon) is a Chimera-like Hollow created by the Quimera Parca ability, made from left arms of Tier Harribel's fraccion.

Name: Bahamut (Final Fantasy)
Summary: A recurring summon in the games, Bahamut is a force to be reckoned as one of the most powerful summons, if not the most powerful summon the player can acquire on their journey. He is most frequently found as part of a sidequest and is not relevant to the main plot, but in some cases he takes a much more active role, such as empowering the Warriors of Light in the original game with their job changes. His demeanor, behavior, and alignment change from appearance to appearance, but all recognize him as the King of Dragons and the Ruler of the Skies.

Name: Blast (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Blast (ブラスト, Burasuto) is the S-Class Rank 1 professional hero of the Hero Association. In the absence of information about Saitama's power, Blast is regarded as the most powerful member of the Hero Association. He currently appears to be traveling to various places in search of God's cubes. Only a few select Hero Association staff members have the means to communicate with him.

Name: Bookworm (My Little Pony)
Key: '''Outside of the Story World''' | '''Inside the Story World'''
Summary: Bookworm was the main antagonist-turned-protagonist during the Storyworld arc of IDWs My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic comics.

Name: Bowser
Summary: Bowser, sometimes known as King Koopa (Japanese: 大魔王クッパ, Daimaō Kuppa or "Great Demon King Koopa"), is the main antagonist of the Mario series and the King of the Koopas. He has repeatedly kidnapped or attempted to kidnap Princess Peach and take over the Mushroom Kingdom. He has also attempted to conquer other lands, such as the Mushroom World, Dinosaur Land, Sprixie Kingdom, and even the entire universe. Despite his villainous nature, he has occasionally helped the heroes of the Mushroom Kingdom against common threats and participates with them in their numerous sporting events in spin-off games.

Name: Captain Ginyu
Summary: nan

Name: Chumbot
Summary: nan

Name: Dennis the Assassin
Summary: nan

Name: Diabolos (Final Fantasy)
Summary: Diabolos is a recurring character in the Final Fantasy franchise, most frequently appearing as an optional boss and summon for the heroes to obtain. He is a demon associated with the power of gravity, darkness, dreams, and sleep, serving as a powerful foe and an equally mighty ally to those able to forge a pact with him.

Name: Doodlebob
Summary: nan

Name: Galaxia
Summary: Galaxia is Meta Knight's sword.

Name: Garou
Key: '''Hero Hunter''' | '''Half-Monster''' | '''Post-Darkshine''' | '''Post-Sage Centipede''' | '''Awakened Garou''' | '''Parallel Timeline Awakened Garou'''
Summary: Saitama: Hey, you got a little better again! Garou: You call this a little?!

Name: Gerard Valkyrie
Summary: Gerard Valkyrie (ジェラルド・ヴァルキリー, Jerarudo Varukirī?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "M" - The Miracle, as well as one of Yhwach's Schutzstaffel (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?, German for "Protective Echelon", Japanese for "Elite/Imperial Guards"). He is also the heart of the Soul King.

Name: God of Darkness
Summary: The God of Darkness is one of the two Gods who created Remnant alongside his older brother, the God of Light. His brother created water, plants and wildlife during the day, while at night, the God of Darkness would discover his sibling's creations and become disgusted. He created drought, fire and famine to destroy them.

Name: God of Light
Summary: The God of Light is one of the two Gods who created Remnant alongside his younger brother, the God of Darkness. The God of Light created water, plants and wildlife during the day, while at night, his brother would discover his sibling's creations and become disgusted. He created drought, fire and famine to destroy them.

Name: Godzilla (GMK)
Summary: The GMK Godzilla (ＧジーＭエムＫケイゴジラ, GMK Gojira?) is a kaiju that appeared in the 2001 Godzilla film, Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack.

Name: Gowasu (Anime)
Summary: Gowasu (ゴワス 'Gowasu') is the Supreme Kai of Universe 10, Zamasu's former master, and Rumsshi's lifelink.

Name: Gremmy Thoumeaux
Summary: Gremmy Thoumeaux (グレミィ・トゥミュー, Guremī Tumyū?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "V" - "The Visionary".

Name: Gumball Watterson
Summary: My brain is amazing; when I find something boring, it actually prevents me from hearing it.

Name: Hero Association
Summary: The Hero Association is an organization founded by the multi-millionaire Agoni after his grandson was saved from a monster by a passerby. Operating independently of the government, the Hero Association recruits various individuals, ordinary and extraordinary alike, to fight for justice against the evil in the world. Those registered within the National Hero Registry database are tasked with protecting civilians from harm against monsters, villains, natural disasters, and other threats and are compensated for their efforts.

Name: Hikone Ubuginu
Summary: Hikone Ubuginu (産絹彦禰, Ubuginu Hikone) a hybrid soul created by Tokinada to become the new Soul King.

Name: Hooleer
Summary: Hooleer is an experimental Hollow reconfiguration by Aizen and the Hogyoku that was eventually killed by Kuna Mashiro.

Name: Ichibē Hyōsube
Summary: Ichibe Hyosube (兵ひょう主す部べ 一いち兵べ衛え, Hyōsube Ichibē?) is the leader of the Royal Guard, known as the Monk who Calls the Real Name (真ま名な呼こ和お尚しょう, Manako Oshō?) thanks to his ability to identify the true names of any being. It was he who named all things in the Soul Society, including Zanpakuto, Shikai, and Bankai, and his own Zanpakuto was the first to reach a second released state.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki Kurosaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Substitute Soul Reaper''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Post-Visored Training''' | '''Final Grimmjow Fight''' | '''Full Hollowfication''' | '''Post-Resurrection''' | '''Post-Dangai Training'''
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ikomikidomoe
Summary: Ikomikidomoe (已己巳己巴) is an ancient Hollow that attacked Soul Society in the past but was defeated by Ichibē Hyōsube and was sealed inside a Zanpakutō by Ōetsu Nimaiya.

Name: Isshin Kurosaki
Summary: Isshin Kurosaki (黒崎 一心, Kurosaki Isshin), formerly known as Isshin Shiba (志波 一心, Shiba Isshin), is the former captain of the 10th Division, husband of Masaki Kurosaki, father of Ichigo Kurosaki, Karin Kurosaki, and Yuzu Kurosaki. Isshin is the former head of a branch of the Shiba Clan and the current head of the Kurosaki family.

Name: Josef (Final Fantasy II)
Summary: Josef is a playable character in Final Fantasy II and one of the primary protagonists of Soul of Rebirth. He was once a soldier of Palamecia, before he escaped and moved to the snowy town of Salamand. He becomes and ally to the party when the rescue to slaves from Semitt Falls. He also helps the party retrieve the Goddess Bell in Snow Cave, but loses his life to a boulder plotted by General Borghen. He then joins the afterlife where he meets Minwu and Scott; joining forces with them in the process.

Name: Karma Noise
Summary: Karma Noise (カルマノイズ) are a new type of Noise that appear in the Senki Zesshō Symphogear XD Unlimited event, Katayoku no Sōsha. Karma Noise are Noise from a parallel world. They first appear during the Zwei Wing concert, where Tsubasa sacrifices herself by singing her Superb Song to destroy them.

Name: Kenpachi Zaraki
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Nnoitora Fight''' | '''Yammy Fight''' | '''Post-SAFWY Novel''' | '''Post-Unohana Training''' | '''CFYOW Novel'''
Summary: Kenpachi Zaraki (更ざら木き 剣八けんぱち, Zaraki Kenpachi?) is the current captain of the 11th Division in the Gotei 13. He is the eleventh Soul Reaper to hold the position and the name Kenpachi, branding him as the strongest Soul Reaper in martial combat. True to his title, Kenpachi is bloodthirsty and reckless, loving nothing more than a good fight and intentionally impairs himself to prolong what would otherwise be an overly swift battle. Despite this, he has some level of compassion for his subordinates, and is rarely seen without his lieutenant and closest friend, Yachiru Kusajishi.

Name: Kirio Hikifune
Summary: Kirio Hikifune (曳舟 桐生, Hikifune Kirio) is a member of the Royal Guard, holding the title "Ruler of Grain" (穀王, Kokuō)

Name: Kisuke Urahara
Key: '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Kisuke Urahara (浦原うらはら 喜き助すけ, Urahara Kisuke?) is the former captain of the 12th Division, as well as the founder and 1st President of the S.R.D.I. His lieutenant was Hiyori Sarugaki. He lives in the Human World where he owns a small convenience store that sells Soul Reaper items. He is assisted by his employees Tessai Tsukabishi, Jinta Hanakari, and Ururu Tsumugiya.

Name: Kraken (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Kraken is the fiend of water. He is the squid like beast that appears in the Sunken Shrine. The Warriors of Light must defeat him to awaken the Water Crystal.

Name: Kugo Ginjo
Summary: Kūgo Ginjō (銀城 空吾, Ginjō Kūgo) is a Fullbringer and was the leader and member No. 001 of the organization known as Xcution. He was the first Substitute Shinigami.

Name: Lich (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Lich is the fiend of Earth and the first of the four fiends fought by the Warriors of Light. He rests at the bottom of Earthgift Shrine and appears to be a skeleton of the undead.

Name: Man Ray
Summary: nan

Name: Marilith (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Marilith is the Fiend of Fire. She appears in Mount Gulg as a woman with the lower body of a snake and has six arms, each wielding a sword.

Name: Master Roshi
Key: '''21st Budōkai''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''Resurrection of F''' | '''Tournament of Power'''
Summary: nan

Name: Mr. Krabs
Summary: nan

Name: Nemu Kurotsuchi
Summary: Nemu Kurotsuchi (涅くろつち ネム, Kurotsuchi Nemu?), formerly known as Nemuri Nanagō (眠ねむり七號ななごう?, Sleeping Number 7), was the lieutenant of the 12th Division of the Gotei 13 formally serving under her father Captain Mayuri Kurotsuchi.

Name: Ozom
Summary: Emperor Ozom was once Jedah Dohma's young confidant, who went under his service to eat the leftover souls of his meals. However, Ozom desired to take Jedah's place as one of the three high nobles of Makai, and set up a plan to usurp his throne. In Makai there is a distortion in space called the Gate, which connects that world to Earth. The Gate is full of energy and swallows everyone who comes near it, which is why it was sealed by the nobles. Ozom decided to convince Jedah to use the energy of the Gate and gain even more power and was then tasked to break only a few seals, to safely maintain the energy output. Instead, Ozom shattered all of them, making it so that when Jedah tried to absorb all the energy bursting out of the gate, it proved too much for him, destroying his body. Ozom's plan had succeeded, and he gathered the remaining power left by the explosion and took over Jedah's estate and his land, becoming the leader of the Dohma family and proclaiming himself emperor. Years later, he resurrected Lord Raptor with the purpose of using him to get rid of the Darkstalkers on Earth and extend his dominion over the planet through his new servant. What Ozom didn't expect was Jedah's resilience, which allowed him to come back from apparent death 100 years later. Jedah returned to his castle, easily removed Ozom and used his soul to create the Majigen, a dimension hosting his plan for the salvation of Makai.

Name: Pernida Parnkgjas
Summary: Pernida Parnkgjas (ペルニダ・パルンカジャス, Perunida Parunkajasu?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter, possessing the designation of "C" - The Compulsory. It is the severed left arm of the Soul King and one of Yhwach's elite Schutzstaffel.

Name: Puffy Fluffy
Summary: nan

Name: Quilge Opie
Summary: Quilge Opie (キルゲ・オピー, Kiruge Opī?) is the "Executive Hunting Captain" (統とう括かつ狩しゅ猟りょう隊たい長ちょう, Tōkatsu Shuryō Taichō?) of the first Jagdarmee of the Wandenreich. He is also a member of the Sternritter with the designation "J" - "The Jail", and is known as Quilge Opie of "the Jail" ("監獄ザ・ジェイル"のキルゲ・オピー, "Za Jeiru" no Kiruge Opī?).

Name: Renji Abarai
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Post-Timeskip''' | '''Post-Royal Guard Training'''
Summary: Renji Abarai (阿散あば井らい 恋れん次じ, Abarai Renji?) is the lieutenant of the 6th Division under Captain Byakuya Kuchiki. He formerly served as the 6th Seat of the 11th Division under Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Retsu Unohana
Summary: Retsu Unohana (卯ノ花 烈, Unohana Retsu), formerly known as Yachiru Unohana (卯ノ花 八千流, Unohana Yachiru), was the captain of the Fourth Division in the Gotei 13. She was one of the oldest and most experienced captains, and was the Soul Society's best healer, as well as the first person to wield the name Kenpachi. Her lieutenant was Isane Kotetsu. She also formerly served as the Captain of the 11th Division.

Name: Ribbon's Shard Gun
Summary: Ribbon’s Shard Gun is the final weapon in Kirby 64. It’s formed from all 72 Crystal Shards.

Name: Romeo (Minecraft)
Summary: Ages ago, Romeo, Xara, and a man named Fred were all living in a simple hut together and were good friends. Sometime later they started adventuring and on their travels, they became "Admins", humans that possessed amazing powers. Possibly, they were once a group of heroes. In their own world, they each built a town for themselves.

Name: Royd Lloyd
Summary: Royd Lloyd ("Rの" ロイド・ロイド, Roido Roido) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "Y" - "The Yourself". He is the identical twin brother of Loyd Lloyd.

Name: Saitama
Summary: Saitama (サイタマ?) is a human from Z-City who; through rigorous (sort of) training broke through his human limiters and achieved unbelievable strength and abilities. Never breaking a sweat, the name One Punch Man is fitting for the effortless wins Saitama has achieved through the series. Never going beyond a simple brawl, his sheer strength, speed, and power have effortlessly mowed down anyone in his way.

Name: Sam Star
Summary: nan

Name: Sandy Cheeks
Summary: nan

Name: Senjumaru Shutara
Summary: Senjumaru Shutara (修しゅ多羅たら 千手丸せんじゅまる, Shutara Senjumaru?) is a member of the Royal Guard, holding the title "Great Weave Guard" (大織守おおおりがみ, Ōorigami?)

Name: Sephiroth (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Before Crisis & Crisis Core''' | '''Final Fantasy VII''' | '''Advent Children''' | '''Dissidia'''
Summary: nan

Name: Sheldon J. Plankton
Summary: nan

Name: Shigekuni Yamamoto Genryusai
Summary: Genryūsai Shigekuni Yamamoto (山やま本もと 元げん柳りゅう斎さい 重しげ國くに, Yamamoto Genryūsai Shigekuni?) was the captain of the Gotei 13's 1st Division and the most powerful Shinigami within Soul Society. Venerated for his power, skill, and wisdom, his word was the ultimate letter of the law in Soul Society.

Name: Shisami
Summary: Shisami (シサミ) is an elite soldier serving Sorbet's elite through Frieza in the Galactic Frieza Army. His name is a pun after "sashimi," a type of food.

Name: Son Gohan (DBS Anime)
Key: '''Resurrection of F''' | '''Universe 6 Tournament''' | '''Tournament of Power''' | '''Super Hero Arc'''
Summary: Son Gohan (孫そん悟ご飯はん?) is the eldest son of Son Goku and Chi-Chi, and one of the primary heroes of the second half of Dragon Ball. Although originally introduced as a mild-mannered and easily scared child, Gohan harbors an immense, limitless potential that surpasses that of his father. However, unlike his father, Gohan dislikes fighting and harming others, and his true power only shows through during moments of intense rage. Following Goku's death, he was trained by Piccolo in anticipation of the upcoming Saiyan invasion, and grew much stronger and closer to his new mentor, ultimately redeeming him and setting him down the path of heroism due to their bond.

Name: Sosuke Aizen
Key: '''Base/First Fusion''' | '''Second Fusion''' | '''Third Fusion''' | '''Fourth Fusion''' | '''Final Fusion''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Sosuke Aizen (藍染あいぜん 惣そう右介すけ, Aizen Sōsuke?) is the former captain of the 5th Division in the Gotei 13. He later leaves Soul Society with his followers, Gin Ichimaru and Kaname Tosen. His lieutenant was Momo Hinamori. He formerly served as the lieutenant of the 5th Division under Shinji Hirako. After waging war against Soul Society with an army of Arrancar, Aizen was defeated by Ichigo Kurosaki and sealed away by Kisuke Urahara, and then imprisoned for his crimes.

Name: Souichi Tomoe (Manga)
Summary: Professor Souichi Tomoe is the leader of the Death Busters, the founder and owner of Mugen Academy. He was originally a scientist well-versed in genetic manipulation and cybernetics who was ostracized by his peers for his unethical experiments to create superhumans, selling some of his findings to companies to buy an entire Tokyo district. When his daughter Hotaru was mortally wounded in a fire that killed her mother Keiko, Tomoe used his knowledge to keep his daughter alive as a cyborg. But at that moment, Tomoe witnessed his assistant being turned into a human-Daimon hybrid and offered himself willing to the Death Busters' cause. His resolve disturbing enough that he willing merged with a Daimon, Tomoe intends to use the Daimons to achieve his goal of creating super beings.

Name: Soul King
Summary: Adnyeus (アドナイェウス, Adonayeusu?), more commonly known as the Soul King (霊れい王おう, Reiō?), is the king of Soul Society, whose existence in Soul Society is as symbolic as it is absolute. The king resides in the Soul King Palace that exists in a separate, special realm in the very core of Soul Society, which is protected by the Royal Guard. The door to this realm is opened via the Ōken.

Name: Squidward Tentacles
Summary: nan

Name: Tagoma
Summary: Tagoma (タゴマ; Tagoma) was one of the elite soldiers working under Sorbet on behalf of Frieza in the Third Stellar Region army of the Frieza Force. His name is a pun on the Japanese word for "egg."

Name: Tenjirō Kirinji
Summary: Tenjirō Kirinji (麒き麟りん寺じ 天てん示じ郎ろう, Kirinji Tenjirō?) is a member of the Royal Guard, holding the title "Hot Spring Demon" (泉せん湯とう鬼き, Sentōki?). Tenjirō holds the position of the First Officer of the Royal Guard as the "Divine General of the East" (東とう方ほう神しん将しょう, Tōhō Shinshō?).

Name: The Console (The Amazing World of Gumball)
Summary: The Game Child (or simply The Console) is a handheld console in The Amazing World of Gumball, serving as an obvious spoof of the Nintendo Game Boy. It was bought by Richard Watterson from The Awesome Store in the episode The Console. It eventually warped the entire town of Elmore into a video game, trapping Gumball, Darwin, Anais, and everybody else.
ID: The Console (The Amazing World of Gumball)-TheAmazingWorldofGumball-4-A

Name: The Flying Dutchman
Summary: nan

Name: The Tattletale Strangler
Summary: nan

Name: Tiamat (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Tiamat is the Fiend of Wind final and most powerful member of the Four Fiends that the Warriors of Light face. She forged a contract with Garland to create an everlasting time loop that would revive the Fiends time and again until the Warriors of Light ventured into the past to end them once and for all.

Name: Tien Shinhan
Key: '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''23rd Budōkai''' | '''Saiyan Arc''' | '''Cell Arc''' | '''Majin Buu Arc''' | '''Tournament of Power
Summary: nan

Name: Tōshirō Hitsugaya
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Post-Timeskip''' | '''Post-Training''' | '''Matured Bankai'''
Summary: Toshiro Hitsugaya (日ひ番つが谷や 冬とう獅し郎ろう, Hitsugaya Tōshirō?) is the captain of the 10th Division in the Gotei 13. His lieutenant is Rangiku Matsumoto. He formerly served as the 3rd Seat of the 10th Division under Isshin Shiba.

Name: Uryū Ishida
Summary: Uryu Ishida (石いし田だ 雨う竜りゅう, Ishida Uryū?) is a Gemischt Quincy residing in Karakura Town. He is a doctor at Karakura Hospital, and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki. He is also a former member of the Wandenreich with the designation "A" - "Antithesis", one of Yhwach's "Schutzstaffel" (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?), and his future successor.

Name: Vincent Valentine
Summary: nan

Name: Wonderweiss Margela
Summary: Wonderweiss Margela (ワンダーワイス・マルジェラ, Wandāwaisu Marujera) is the 77th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and the only modified Arrancar under Aizen's command. Though not an actual Espada, Soul Society ranks his Spiritual Energy in the same class as theirs.

Name: Yhwach
Summary: Yhwach (ユーハバッハ, Yūhabahha?) is the Father of the Quincy, the monarch of the Wandenreich, and the son of the Soul King, known by the designation "A" - The Almighty.

Name: Yoruichi Shihoin
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yoruichi Shihōin (四楓院 夜一, Shihōin Yoruichi) is the former captain of the 2nd Division of the Gotei 13, as well as the former commander of the Onmitsukido. Her lieutenant was Marenoshin Omaeda. Having abandoned her command of both positions, she works with Kisuke Urahara and Tessai Tsukabishi, based in the Urahara Shop out in the Human World.

Name: Zetton
Key: '''Ultraman (Generation I)''' | '''Return of Ultraman (Generation II)''' | '''Ultraman: The Ultimate Hero (Powered)''' | '''Ultraman Max''' | '''Ultraman Mebius''' | '''Ultraman Mebius Gaiden: Ghost Rebirth (EX)''' | '''Ultraman X''' | '''Ultraman Orb (Maga)''' | '''Ultraman Taiga''' | '''Ultra Galaxy Fight: The Absolute Conspiracy'''
Summary: Zetton, is a giant, horned, humanoid, beetle-like Kaiju that served as the final and strongest monster of the original Ultraman series.

Name: Ōetsu Nimaiya
Summary: Ōetsu Nimaiya (二枚屋 王悦, Nimaiya Ōetsu) is a member of the Royal Guard, holding the title "God of the Sword" (刀神, Tōshin).

Name: Akira Yuki (Godzilla)
Summary: Major Akira Yuki (結城 晃) is a G-Force soldier and the main human protagonist in the 1994 Godzilla film Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla. He is committed to getting revenge on Godzilla for causing the death of his best friend, Colonel Goro Gondo, during the events of the film Godzilla vs Biollante.

Name: Battra
Summary: Battra (バトラ Batora) is a dark divine moth kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1992 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mothra. In the film, he was seen as a sort of "evil" counterpart to Mothra, at least early on.

Name: Cell (Manga)
Summary: Cell (セル, Seru?) is the ultimate creation of Dr. Gero, created from the DNA of the greatest fighters to ever visit Earth and tasked with the simple goal of killing Son Goku. However, to reach his perfect form and full power, Cell must absorb Gero's other biomechanical creations; the Androids, 17 and 18.

Name: Dabura
Summary: Dabura (ダーブラ) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga and in the anime Dragon Ball Z. He is the ruler of the Demon Realm. His name is originally taken from the last half of the famous incantation, "Abracadabra".

Name: Destoroyah
Summary: Destoroyah (デストロイア, Desutoroia?, lit. Destroyer) is a crustacean kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1995 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Destoroyah. Originally a colony of microscopic Precambrian crustaceans that mutated from exposure to the Oxygen Destroyer used to kill the first Godzilla in 1954, it created a monster able to splinter itself and recombine at will. Named after the biological weapon that created it, Destoroyah is the final opponent of Burning Godzilla in his final moments.

Name: Future Trunks (DBS Manga)
Key: '''Majin Buu Arc''' | '''Early Goku Black Arc''' | '''Post-Gravity Training'''
Summary: Future Trunks (未み来らいのトランクス, Mirai no Torankusu?) referred to in the series simply as Trunks, is the Saiyan and Human hybrid son of Vegeta and Bulma from the alternate future. After the events of the Cell Games, Future Trunks is later found and trained by Shin and Kibito in preparation for Babidi coming to Earth in order to revive Majin Buu. Even after the threat of Majin Buu was neutralized, later appeared a more powerful and terrifying threat. With the arrival of Goku Black, Trunks' future returned to ruin on a scale never seen before. It's now up to him to save the future with the help of Goku and Vegeta once again.

Name: Garoga Compactor
Summary: The Garoga Compactor is one of the strongest Garogas weapons designed to kill Zone Fighter once and for all.

Name: Garogas
Summary: The Garogas (ガロガ星人) are an evil alien race created by Toho that first appeared in the 1973 tokusatsu kaiju series, Zone Fighter.

Name: Garuda (Godzilla)
Summary: The Garuda (ガルーダ) is a mechanical vehicle created by Toho that first appeared in the 1993 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla II. It attaches to Mechagodzilla, creating Super Mechagodzilla.

Name: Godzilla (Heisei)
Key: '''Godzillasaurus''' | '''Return of Godzilla/vs. Biollante (Pre-Supercharge)''' | '''vs. King Ghidorah/vs. Mothra (Post-Supercharge)''' | '''vs. Mechagodzilla/Post-Rodan Boost''' | '''vs. SpaceGodzilla''' | '''Burning Godzilla'''
Summary: In the 1970s, a nuclear submarine crashed in the Bering Sea. A Godzillasaurus, barely hanging on to life in the cold ocean depths, was heavily mutated to a staggering height of 80 meters. This dinosaur had been relocated to this remote area by time travelers from the 23rd century, but little did they realize that their actions would actually fulfill the course of history and create the Godzilla they had sought to destroy...

Name: Godzilla Jr.
Key: '''Baby Godzilla''' | '''Little Godzilla''' | '''Godzilla Jr.''' | '''Rebirth Godzilla''' | '''Post-Rebirth''' | '''Powered Up State'''
Summary: Godzilla Jr (ゴジラジュニア, Gojira Junia?), also known as Baby Godzilla (ベビーゴジラ, Bebī Gojira?) and Little Godzilla (リトルゴジラ, Ritoru Gojira?), is a young Godzillasaurus kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1993 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla II.

Name: Goku Black (Manga)
Summary: Zamasu (ザマス?) was once the Supreme Kai apprentice under Gowasu of Universe 10, who developed a loathing for mortals as he witnessed their actions across the universe, leading him to embark on a crusade against mortals after stealing the body of Son Goku using the Super Dragon Balls, gaining the title of Goku Black (悟ご空くうブラック, Gokū Burakku?), or, as he is more commonly referred, simply Black.|

Name: Gomora
Key: '''Ultraman (Generation I)''' | '''Ultraman 80 (Generation II)''' | '''Ultraman: The Ultimate Hero (Powered)''' | '''Ultraman Max (Generation III)''' | '''Ultraman Mebius (Generation IV)''' | '''Ultraman Ginga S''' | '''Ultraman R/B''' | '''Ultraman Z'''
Summary: Gomora is an ancient kaiju species from Earth. Gomora is supposedly portrayed as a hostile Kaiju, starting with the emergence of Rei's Gomora, most later incarnations of them are portrayed as comrades to respective protagonists of the series.

Name: Gotenks
Key: '''Pre-Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Post-Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Super Saiyan 3''' | '''Super Hero Arc'''
Summary: nan

Name: Hikone Ubuginu
Summary: Hikone Ubuginu (産絹彦禰, Ubuginu Hikone) a hybrid soul created by Tokinada to become the new Soul King.

Name: Ichibē Hyōsube
Summary: Ichibe Hyosube (兵ひょう主す部べ 一いち兵べ衛え, Hyōsube Ichibē?) is the leader of the Royal Guard, known as the Monk who Calls the Real Name (真ま名な呼こ和お尚しょう, Manako Oshō?) thanks to his ability to identify the true names of any being. It was he who named all things in the Soul Society, including Zanpakuto, Shikai, and Bankai, and his own Zanpakuto was the first to reach a second released state.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki Kurosaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Substitute Soul Reaper''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Post-Visored Training''' | '''Final Grimmjow Fight''' | '''Full Hollowfication''' | '''Post-Resurrection''' | '''Post-Dangai Training'''
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ikomikidomoe
Summary: Ikomikidomoe (已己巳己巴) is an ancient Hollow that attacked Soul Society in the past but was defeated by Ichibē Hyōsube and was sealed inside a Zanpakutō by Ōetsu Nimaiya.

Name: Kenpachi Zaraki
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Nnoitora Fight''' | '''Yammy Fight''' | '''Post-SAFWY Novel''' | '''Post-Unohana Training''' | '''CFYOW Novel'''
Summary: Kenpachi Zaraki (更ざら木き 剣八けんぱち, Zaraki Kenpachi?) is the current captain of the 11th Division in the Gotei 13. He is the eleventh Soul Reaper to hold the position and the name Kenpachi, branding him as the strongest Soul Reaper in martial combat. True to his title, Kenpachi is bloodthirsty and reckless, loving nothing more than a good fight and intentionally impairs himself to prolong what would otherwise be an overly swift battle. Despite this, he has some level of compassion for his subordinates, and is rarely seen without his lieutenant and closest friend, Yachiru Kusajishi.

Name: King Ghidorah (Heisei)
Summary: In Godzilla vs. King Ghidorah, King Ghidorah is part of a scheme by time-traveling terrorists known as the Futurians to destroy Japan in the past to prevent it from becoming a global economic superpower. He is the result of the Futurians placing three genetically-engineered creatures from the future called Dorats on Lagos Island in the year 1944. In 1954, the Dorats were exposed to the Castle Bravo hydrogen bomb test conducted at nearby Bikini Atoll, which caused them to merge and mutate into King Ghidorah.

Name: Kirio Hikifune
Summary: Kirio Hikifune (曳舟 桐生, Hikifune Kirio) is a member of the Royal Guard, holding the title "Ruler of Grain" (穀王, Kokuō)

Name: Kiyoshi Sato
Summary: Kiyoshi Sato (佐藤清志) is a G-Force lieutenant and a supporting character in the 1994 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla.

Name: Koji Shinjo
Summary: Koji Shinjo (新城功二) is one of the main human protagonists in the 1994 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla. He is a lieutenant in G-Force and a co-pilot of MOGUERA.

Name: Kugo Ginjo
Summary: Kūgo Ginjō (銀城 空吾, Ginjō Kūgo) is a Fullbringer and was the leader and member No. 001 of the organization known as Xcution. He was the first Substitute Shinigami.

Name: Lord Garmadon
Summary: Lord Garmadon is one of the 2 children of The First Spinjitzu Master, and is the older brother to Sensei Wu. Once a noble and good-natured child (if somewhat jealous of his brother), he was bitten by the Great Devourer, an ancient snake mutated by the power of The Overlord. The venom of the Great Devourer began to change his personality, slowly making him into an evil and cruel person. Though this was at first imperceptible, the evil in his veins slowly began to manifest. Garmadon then became the student of the evil cultist Master Chen, who granted him the title of lordship. Chen also encouraged him to pursue a young Misako, who his brother was also wooing, by stealing a letter from Wu and claiming it to be his. After Chen's manipulation of the Serpentine and Ninjago's citizens led to war between the two factions, Garmadon rejoined his brother and the Elemental Masters, ultimately defeating the Serpentine and forcing them underground.

Name: M.O.G.U.E.R.A.
Summary: M.O.G.U.E.R.A. (ＭＯＧＥＲＡ Mogera) is a U.N.-built mecha created by Toho that first appeared in the 1994 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla. The M.O.G.U.E.R.A. acronym stands for "Mobile Operation Godzilla Universal Expert Robot Aero-type."

Name: Majin Buu
Summary: nan

Name: MBAW-93
Summary: The MBAW-93 (９３式) is a Maser-based tank which first appeared in the 1992 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mothra.

Name: Mechagodzilla (Heisei)
Summary: The Heisei Mechagodzilla (メカゴジラ Mekagojira), also known as Super Mechagodzilla (スーパーメカゴジラ Sūpā Mekagojira), is a mecha created by Toho that first appeared in the 1993 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla 2.

Name: Megath
Summary: Megath are a race of giants residing in the second Demon World on the planet Mega. Although they have immense strength, they are often not fighters and choose not to use it.

Name: Mogra (Ninjago)
Summary: Mogra was the leader of the Red Crow and a former ally of the Elemental Alliance before defecting to the side of Chen and the Serpentine during the Serpentine War. He eventually got defeated by Wu and Garmadon before getting executed. Later, after the defeat of Emperor Garmadon, he somehow came back to life, seeking revenge against Garmadon and assembling his own army in order to destroy him

Name: Mothra (Heisei)
Summary: Mothra (モスラ, Mosura?) is a giant divine moth kaiju that first appeared in the 1992 Godzilla film Godzilla vs. Mothra.

Name: Renji Abarai
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Post-Timeskip''' | '''Post-Royal Guard Training'''
Summary: Renji Abarai (阿散あば井らい 恋れん次じ, Abarai Renji?) is the lieutenant of the 6th Division under Captain Byakuya Kuchiki. He formerly served as the 6th Seat of the 11th Division under Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Rita Repulsa
Summary: Rita Repulsa was initially the primary antagonist of Mighty Morphin' Power Rangers, though was eventually shoved to the side by her much more powerful and commanding husband, Lord Zedd.

Name: Rodan (Heisei)
Summary: Rodan (ラドン) is a giant Pteranodon kaiju that appeared in the 1993 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla II.

Name: Senjumaru Shutara
Summary: Senjumaru Shutara (修しゅ多羅たら 千手丸せんじゅまる, Shutara Senjumaru?) is a member of the Royal Guard, holding the title "Great Weave Guard" (大織守おおおりがみ, Ōorigami?)

Name: Shin (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Shin is the East Supreme Kai (or East Kaioshin) of Universe 7, responsible for the oversight of the eastern quadrant of the living universe and, ultimately, the entire universe, with the deaths of his fellow Kai.

Name: Son Gohan (Dragon Ball Z)
Key: '''Saiyan Arc''' | '''Frieza Arc to Early Cell Arc''' | '''Post-Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''25th Budōkai''' | '''Post-Majin Buu Fight'''
Summary: Son Gohan is the eldest son of Son Goku and Chi-Chi, and one of the primary heroes of the second half of Dragon Ball. Unlike his father, Gohan was a timid and studious child who lacked the Saiyan fighting spirit despite possessing enormous strength inside him. Nonetheless, Gohan spends much of his youth defending Earth with the rest of the heroes, eventually becoming one of the most formidable Z-Fighters. After reaching adulthood in peacetime, he finally fulfils his dream of becoming a scholar.

Name: Son Goku (Dragon Ball Z)
Key: '''Beginning of Z''' | '''Post-North Kai Training''' | '''Post-Gravity Training''' | '''Frieza Fight''' | '''Early Cell Arc''' | '''Post-Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Majin Buu Arc'''
Summary: Trunks: ...Why didn't you get out of the way? Goku: Because I didn't feel any malice. I knew you were going to stop.

Name: Sosuke Aizen
Key: '''Base/First Fusion''' | '''Second Fusion''' | '''Third Fusion''' | '''Fourth Fusion''' | '''Final Fusion''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Sosuke Aizen (藍染あいぜん 惣そう右介すけ, Aizen Sōsuke?) is the former captain of the 5th Division in the Gotei 13. He later leaves Soul Society with his followers, Gin Ichimaru and Kaname Tosen. His lieutenant was Momo Hinamori. He formerly served as the lieutenant of the 5th Division under Shinji Hirako. After waging war against Soul Society with an army of Arrancar, Aizen was defeated by Ichigo Kurosaki and sealed away by Kisuke Urahara, and then imprisoned for his crimes.

Name: Soul King
Summary: Adnyeus (アドナイェウス, Adonayeusu?), more commonly known as the Soul King (霊れい王おう, Reiō?), is the king of Soul Society, whose existence in Soul Society is as symbolic as it is absolute. The king resides in the Soul King Palace that exists in a separate, special realm in the very core of Soul Society, which is protected by the Royal Guard. The door to this realm is opened via the Ōken.

Name: SpaceGodzilla (Heisei)
Summary: SpaceGodzilla (スペースゴジラ, Supēsu Gojira?) is a heavily-modified Godzilla clone kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1994 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla.

Name: Super X3
Summary: The Super X3 (スーパーＸＩＩＩ) is an aerial vehicle used by G-Force that first appeared in the 1995 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Destoroyah.

Name: Tamagami Number One
Summary: Tamagami Number One (タマガミ・ナンバー・ワン, Tamagami Nanbā Wan?) is one of the three Tamagami that were created by Neva in order to protect the Demon Realm's Dragon Balls. Because of the strength of the Tamagami, no one in Demon Realm history before Son Goku's group were able to have their wish granted. It resides in the first Demon Realm.

Name: Tamagami Number Three
Summary: Tamagami Number Three (タマガミ・ナンバー・スリー, Tamagami Nanbā Surī?) is one of the three Tamagami that were created by Neva in order to protect the Demon Realm's Dragon Balls. Because of the strength of the Tamagami, no one in Demon Realm history before Son Goku's group were able to have their wish granted. It resides in the third Demon Realm.

Name: Tamagami Number Two
Summary: Tamagami Number Two (タマガミ・ナンバー・ツー, Tamagami Nanbā Tsū?) is one of the three Tamagami that were created by Neva in order to protect the Demon Realm's Dragon Balls. Because of the strength of the Tamagami, no one in Demon Realm history before Son Goku's group were able to have their wish granted. It resides in the second Demon Realm.

Name: Tenjirō Kirinji
Summary: Tenjirō Kirinji (麒き麟りん寺じ 天てん示じ郎ろう, Kirinji Tenjirō?) is a member of the Royal Guard, holding the title "Hot Spring Demon" (泉せん湯とう鬼き, Sentōki?). Tenjirō holds the position of the First Officer of the Royal Guard as the "Divine General of the East" (東とう方ほう神しん将しょう, Tōhō Shinshō?).

Name: The Last Prime (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: The Last Prime was the last surviving member of the Dynasty of Primes, who were the first Transformers created by the Allspark. He used the last remnants of his power and energy to seal away the Fallen and created a tomb to hide the Matrix, the key to the Star Harvester.

Name: Tommy Oliver
Key: '''Civilian''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 1''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 2''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 3''' | '''Red Zeo Form''' | '''Dino Thunder Black''' | '''Super Dino Mode'''
Summary: Tommy Oliver is the Green Mighty Morphin Ranger, White Mighty Morphin Ranger, Red Zeo Ranger, Red Turbo Ranger I & the Black Dino Ranger. He is often considered the greatest Power Ranger of all time both in and out of the actual show for his many accomplishments on several different teams. He is a fan favorite, the most reoccurring ranger, and second most reoccurring character in the entire show next to Bulk. He is also one of the strongest rangers.

Name: Ultraman (Ultra Series)
Key: '''Showa Era''' | '''Heisei Era''' | '''Galaxy Crisis Era''' | '''New Generation Era (Before Crisis)''' | '''New Generation Era (After Crisis)''' | '''Reiwa Era'''
Summary: Mefilas: "What are you Ultraman? Are you an alien, or a human?" Ultraman: "I am both. I was born to fight those who break universal laws, like you"

Name: Unicron (IDW)
Summary: In the early days of Cybertron's history, Unicron was viewed as Cybertron's greatest enemy. It was told that he was arch nemesis of the mythical Primus, and would one day be destined to awakened once again to attack Cybertron, and was destined to be slain by the last of the Primes.

Name: Uryū Ishida
Summary: Uryu Ishida (石いし田だ 雨う竜りゅう, Ishida Uryū?) is a Gemischt Quincy residing in Karakura Town. He is a doctor at Karakura Hospital, and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki. He is also a former member of the Wandenreich with the designation "A" - "Antithesis", one of Yhwach's "Schutzstaffel" (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?), and his future successor.

Name: Vegeta (DBS Manga)
Key: '''Battle of Gods Arc''' | '''Resurrection 'F' Arc''' | '''Universe 6 - Future Trunks Arc''' | '''Post-Training Future Trunks Saga''' | '''Universe Survival - Broly Arc''' | '''Galactic Patrol Prisoner Arc''' | '''Granolah the Survivor Arc'''
Summary: Vegeta (ベジータ, Bejīta?) is the disgraced prince of the Saiyan race, one of the few survivors of his species after Frieza destroyed Planet Vegeta. Left with no choice but to follow his orders, Vegeta travelled across the galaxy and eradicated planets for sale before he was brought to Earth by Raditz's report of the Dragon Balls, a magical set of balls that could grant him immortality. Upon arriving on Earth, he ultimately comes to encounter and fights Son Goku, the man who would go on to become his greatest rival.

Name: Vegeta (Dragon Ball Z)
Key: '''Saiyan Arc''' | '''Early Frieza Arc''' | '''Late Frieza Arc''' | '''Early Cell Arc''' | '''Post-First Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Post-Second Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Majin Buu Arc'''
Summary: Vegeta (ベジータ, Bejīta?) is the disgraced prince of the Saiyan race, one of the few survivors of his species after Frieza destroyed Planet Vegeta. Left with no choice but to follow his orders, Vegeta travelled across the galaxy and eradicated planets for sale before he was brought to Earth by Raditz's report of the Dragon Balls, a magical set of balls that could grant him immortality. Upon arriving on Earth, he ultimately comes to encounter and fights Son Goku, the man who would go on to become his greatest rival.

Name: Vegito
Summary: nan

Name: Yhwach
Summary: Yhwach (ユーハバッハ, Yūhabahha?) is the Father of the Quincy, the monarch of the Wandenreich, and the son of the Soul King, known by the designation "A" - The Almighty.

Name: Zetton
Key: '''Ultraman (Generation I)''' | '''Return of Ultraman (Generation II)''' | '''Ultraman: The Ultimate Hero (Powered)''' | '''Ultraman Max''' | '''Ultraman Mebius''' | '''Ultraman Mebius Gaiden: Ghost Rebirth (EX)''' | '''Ultraman X''' | '''Ultraman Orb (Maga)''' | '''Ultraman Taiga''' | '''Ultra Galaxy Fight: The Absolute Conspiracy'''
Summary: Zetton, is a giant, horned, humanoid, beetle-like Kaiju that served as the final and strongest monster of the original Ultraman series.

Name: Zoffy
Key: '''Showa Era''' | '''Heisei Era''' | '''Galaxy Crisis Era''' | '''New Generation Era (Pre-Crisis)''' | '''New Generation Era (Post-Crisis)''' | '''Reiwa Era'''
Summary: Human, you've come this far under your own power. Before long, the time will come that you'll stand side by side with us, and soar across the gulf of the stars. Until then, we will be the shield for your world. I look forward to our next meeting

Name: Ōetsu Nimaiya
Summary: Ōetsu Nimaiya (二枚屋 王悦, Nimaiya Ōetsu) is a member of the Royal Guard, holding the title "God of the Sword" (刀神, Tōshin).

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Anguirus (Showa)
Key: '''First Generation''' | '''Second Generation''' | '''Second Generation End of Showa era'''
Summary: Anguirus is a four-legged dinosaur-like creature that looks similar to an ankylosaurus. He has several horns at the top of his head and a single horn above his nose like a rhinoceros. His face is long and drawn out, like a crocodile, and has rows of jagged, serrated teeth. His carapace is studded with long, sharp spikes. Anguirus' tail is longer than his body and makes up most of his body length, and is also covered with spikes. His hind limbs are longer than his forelimbs, enabling him to stand up on them to his full height, but he generally walks on all fours.

Name: Ash (Ninjago)
Summary: Ash is the current Elemental Master of Smoke and was a fierce competitor in Master Chen's Tournament of Elements, alongside the other Elemental Masters of his generation. In the third round of the event, Ash fought against Kai inside a volcano, where he proved himself to be a dangerous and very skilled adversary. After a long fight, Kai claimed the Jadeblade and defeated Ash. Afterward, he was ridden of his powers and forced to work in Chen's noodle factory. Later, Ash would ally with the other Elemental Masters to reclaim their powers.

Name: Balgaras
Summary: Balgaras (バルガラス) is a kaiju created by Toho that appeared in episode 17 of the 1973 Tokusatsu Kaiju series, Zone Fighter, titled Go! Fighter, Scramble.

Name: Barakidon
Summary: Barakidon (バラキドン) is a kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 12th episode of Zone Fighter, The Terror-Beast Base: Invade the Earth!.

Name: Benthomaar
Summary: King Benthomaar is the current ruler of Merlopia and the Endless Sea, Trimaar's adopted son and Kalmaar's adoptive brother. As a kid, he was adopted by King Trimaar of Merlopia, becoming the brother of Prince Kalmaar. Through the years, Benthomaar tried to convince Kalmaar to accept him as his brother, but he never succeeded. Years later, when Kalmaar became closer to awaken the sea serpent Wojira, he joined force with the Ninjas and stopped his evil brother from destroying the surface world.

Name: Blade Master Bansha
Summary: "Blade Master" Bansha is a secondary antagonist of the 5th Season of Ninjago. She is one of the 5 generals of the Ghost Warrior Army, and a powerful sorceress. Her main weapon is a Double-Bladed Dagger, and she resides in the Cursed Realm. She was summoned by Morro using the Allied Armor of Azure, alongside Soul Archer and Ghoultar to help him getting the Sword of Sanctuary in the Cloud Kingdom, which was the key to find the Realm Crystal, an object necessary to free their master, the Preeminent, form the Cursed Realm.

Name: Bolobo
Summary: Bolobo is the current Elemental Master of Nature. He was a competitor in Master Chen's Tournament of Elements, alongside the other Elemental Masters of his generation. In the second round of the event, Bolobo fought against Neuro, who used his element to mess with Bolobo's mind and eventually defeat him by securing the Jadeblade. Afterward, Bolobo was ridden of his powers and forced to work in Chen's noodle factory. Eventually, Bolobo united with the other Elemental Masters to restore their elements.

Name: Bow Master Soul Archer
Summary: "Bow Master" Soul Archer is a secondary antagonist of the 5th Season of Ninjago. He is one of the 5 generals of the Ghost Warrior Army, his main weapons are Bow and Arrow, and he resides in the Cursed Realm. He was summoned by Morro using the Allied Armor of Azure, alongside Ghoultar and Bansha to help him getting the Sword of Sanctuary in the Cloud Kingdom, which was the key to find the Realm Crystal, an object necessary to free their master, the Preeminent, form the Cursed Realm.

Name: Chain Master Wrayth
Summary: "Chain Master" Wrayth is a secondary antagonist of the 5th Season of Ninjago. He is one of the 5 generals of the Ghost Warrior Army, his main weapon is the Chain Whip, and he resides in the Cursed Realm. He was summoned by Morro to defeat the Ninjas while they were still powerless. He possessed a motorcycle that he found and ambushed the Ninjas while they were traveling and after a tough battle, he was defeated.

Name: Chamille
Summary: Chamille is the current Elemental Master of Form and was a competitor in Master Chen's Tournament of Elements, alongside the other Elemental Masters of her generation. Chamille competed against Lloyd in the Thunderblade round, a game where Elemental Masters can choose whom to side with. The ninja sided with Lloyd while everyone else stood with Chamille. After an intense series of obstacles and attacks mainly from Chamille and her group, Lloyd won the round, but Chen tried to disqualify him anyway. The Elemental Masters threatened to quit the game if he did so, forcing Chen to announce Chamille as the loser. Afterward, she was ridden of her powers and forced to work in Chen's noodle factory. Eventually, Chamille would ally with the other Elemental Masters to reclaim their elements.

Name: Cinder (Ninjago)
